text_retweet:
#repost @ftmmagazine (@get_repost)
・・・
razor manufacturer gillete, a proctor & gamble brand, released a two minute commercial that addresses toxic behaviors and incubation of toxic masculinity. gillette’s tag line “the best a man can get” has been turned into a question as a narrator voices over the images of bullying, “boys will be boys” chants and news reports of the “me too” movement chants to name a few. later in the ad they show men sticking up for others as a nod to the “me too movement”. “is this the best a man can get? is it? we can’t hide from it. it has been going on far too long. we can’t laugh it off, making the same old excuses,” a narrator declares. 
gillette is utilizing their platform to hold each other accountable for behavior - and they have now placed themselves as a very visible company, dedicating themselves to promoting positive, attainable, and inclusive versions of what it means to be a man. (really, a good human. ) 
this is sparking outrage, but personally let’s believe it sparks the foot steps to a bigger conversation and changing the climate. hats off to you, @gillette . i strongly encourage you all to watch the ad. find the video here, link is in our story as well. : https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=kopmueyp3a0 // author: @ajfaiella .
.
.
.
.
tags| #ftm #trans #ftmmagazine #transmen #transgender #gillette #metoo #metoomovement #ally #support #ajf #shaving #rally #transrightsarehumanrights #rights #equality #toxicmasculinity

text:
ayer salió un anuncio de gillette haciendo una crítica al hombre actual y a la masculinidad tóxica que ha dado mucho de que hablar. además, muchos hombres y mujeres han criticado el anuncio y éste se ha hecho bastante viral.

analizándolo objetivamente, creo que gillette se ha pegado un tiro en su propio pie, ya que han puesto en su contra a muchos hombres, que son el público principal de esta empresa.

el anuncio empieza hablando del #metoo, el cual ha sido bastante discutido a raíz de diversas acusaciones de delitos a la líder del movimiento. también insinúa que el bullying únicamente lo causan personas del género masculino. luego sacan un clip de unas películas de unos 50 años dónde se visibiliza un acoso a la mujer en algunos ámbitos (lo cual obviamente me parece mal, pero que hayan usado películas de hace medio siglo ya dice bastante). también sacan el mansplaining, ya que ahora parece que ser hombre y corregir a una mujer te pone en una situación de superioridad. estos han sido los temas más notables, pero en general parece que por culpa de una minoría, se criminaliza al hombre y se le trata como un animal al que hay que educar para que actúe de la forma correcta.

parece que está aceptado hacer un anuncio que generaliza con los estereotipos masculinos, pero que no critiquen al feminismo, a la transexualidad o a los 'oprimidos' en general, que vienen los ofendiditos a tirar el anuncio y a demandar.

aún así todo esto es marketing, y las empresas con esto no buscan gustar o dejar de gustar, sino sacar beneficio. no creo que haya que ofenderse por esto, ya que estaríamos poniéndonos del lado de aquellos que tanto criticamos. por otro lado, no veo que se anuncie un producto, lo cual debería ser primordial, pero parece que a gillette el tema del marketing viral no se le da muy bien.

por cierto, bien por el anuncio moralmente superior, pero para la próxima habría que acordarse de que hace poco gillette se vio envuelto en una polémica por usar niños para trabajos forzados. ah no, que de eso no se habla.

anuncio demandar . aún así todo esto e marketing , la empresas con esto buscan gustar dejar de gustar , sino sacar beneficio . creo que haya que ofenderse por esto , ya que estaríamos poniéndonos del lado de aquellos que tanto criticamos . por otro lado , veo que se anuncie un producto , lo cual debería ser primordial , pero parece que gillette el tema del marketing viral se le da muy bien . por cieo , bien por el anuncio moralmente superior , pero para la próxima habría que acordarse de que hace poco gillette se vio envuelto en una polémica por usar niños para trabajos forzados . ah , que de eso se habla .

text:
in the days following gillette's ad campaign promoting a new kind of positive masculinity, there seems to be sides taken by those against and those for its message. "bullying. harassment. is this the best a man can get? it's only by challenging ourselves to do more, that we can get closer to our best. instead of excuses, we need to make a change. we are taking action at www.thebestmencanbe.org. join us." if your masculinity is threatened by that message - you're doing masculinity wrong.

as someone who grew up with two older brothers, and was bullied in school - i know a lot about perceived masculinity and the ad nailed so much of it perfectly. this ad doesn't suggest all men are this way, but we know a lot of them are. we see them at work or school, online or in public. bernice king, daughter of the late civil rights legend martin luther king has said "this commercial isn’t anti-male. it’s pro-humanity," and that "it demonstrates that character can step up to change conditions". the excuses for bad behavior (as if anything else is feminine) and the backlash against this ad only reveals the necessity for more just like it. more dialogue with your kids (of any gender), friends, co-workers - whomever wants to listen will only strengthen the cause and help save lives. if you think i'm overstating, i would remind anyone fighting these ideas that the headlines have already been written; male suicide rates and the incel movement are two damning issues that come to mind when i think of the current culture of men. if this ad to help sell razors helps just a handful of boys and men grow up to be the best man he can be, then it was worth the uproar.

as a father to a boy, you have these ideas of how they will be when they're older and what wisdom you're passing down. you also might unknowingly be passing down how you act towards people (them, their mother, sister etc). i know better than i did years ago, months ago, maybe even days. i know i'm not perfect and that i don't have to hide behind masculinity to say otherwise; i will encourage being better.

text:
“unruliness isn’t just calling attention to arbitrary expectations of how a woman should behave. it’s also a willingness to expect better for all other women - and better of oneself.” ~anne helen petersen 👣 
for all the ladies hitting the street this weekend. 
this is not a quick read, not because it isn’t written well, but because the ideas should be given time to marinate in our own brains. there are hundreds of years of force fed bs we must deal with in some of these chapters. and like many of us know, we women are just as guilty of holding ourselves and other women down as men are. 
i purposely took this read slower because i wanted to receive the message without anger. anger is easy, but opening your eyes to behavior you yourself exhibit with or without realizing you are doing it requires you to be present and not projecting this on the big bad world. 
@annehelenpetersen has done a great job of showing the hypocrisy professional women deal with, while at the same time showing how these women have pioneered growth for women. this is not an angry book, but one that shows hope for a more inclusive world for women so long as we are willing to see the world, ourselves, and those around us for what it really is.

text:
hey y’all 👀
it’s been a while but i’ve been quietly crafting and healing and deep diving. .
.
.
i’m christi g. licensed therapist, self empowerment specialist... i have a background in mindfulness and dance meditation. i love to #getoutside ... ocean 🌊 or mountain 🏔 side ... and i have been all over this planet to some incredible places. temples in india, facing grizzly bears in denali national park alaska, riding my motorcycle around hawaii, working and living in europe, healing from cancer, stepping up my game from #metoo victim of sexual assault to a power house of women’s empowerment ... i have seen 100 tinder dates, worked my way out of debt, met my dreamy soon to be husband and started my own business. .
.
.
i’m here to help you find the life of your dreams too. a little bit of deep reflection, discovering desire, mapping out a plan and infusing it with devotion- will start things in motion that will carry you to a new way of being. it’s the small steps that will change your entire life. .
.
.
let’s live it together- because we heal in community, we rise in community and we need each other in so many ways. you don’t have to do it alone. .
.
.
#selfempowermentjourney

text:
mel ramos (1935-2018)
mel ramos, roy lichtenstein and andy warhol exhibited together in a seminal show at the los angeles county #museum of art in 1963. it was the era of #playboy (then a publishing phenomenon) and of marshall mcluhan’s ‘the medium is the message’ #analysis of #advertising manipulation. ramos’ ironic commentaries on the use of #sex to sell any commodity (and the californian obsession with the body beautiful) reflected other #american artists’ – like claes oldenburg, james rosenquist, tom wesselmann and wayne thiebaud – reaction to the soft power of popular culture and the mass media. #popart art rapidly became an influential movement that still resonates today, and ramos is regarded as a key participant in its evolution.

initially the feminist movement of the 1970s, and now current social issues concerned with misogyny and the #metoo movement, have redefined ramos’ work as controversial. even his depictions of famous comic book characters have come under negative scrutiny, when re-viewed through the lens of contemporary sensibilities. nevertheless, his confrontational use of the female nude, configured with branded products, to generate an ‘instant recognition’ factor, has paved the way for the uninhibited, sexualised subject matter common in 21st century post-pop art.

the #art of mel ramos is included in the whitney museum of american art; museum of modern art in new york; and a major exhibition was held at the albertina in vienna in 2011. his first solo show in the uk is at the bermondsey project space in 2019.

ramos was art professor at california state university, east bay (1966 -97), and emeritus professor (1998-2018).
name: Bermondsey Project Space

text:
10yrs can really change a person. 10yrs ago, 16, i was clawing my way out of an abusive relationship - not recognizing i was being abused. i knew what was happening wasn’t right, but when you’re that young, “in love” for the first time, you tend to turn a blind eye to it. you put on an act, you cover it with a smile and some makeup, and you keep  moving. you lie to every single person that cares about you, “he’s great. he’s so sweet. he treats me well. we’re so happy.” and eventually you start to believe your own bullshit.

physical abuse, sexual abuse, emotional abuse are all real things that people endure everyday. it’s not a “cry for attention,” or “made up.” it’s so fucking real. and it messes up your definition of love for a really long time. 
10yrs later, i am the strongest version of myself, that i’ve ever been, and i will never stop working on myself; striving to be better and better and better. if i could go back and tell that girl anything, it would be. 1. this pain makes you stronger 2. it’s not your fault. 3. you did not deserve that. when my daughter is here, i will make damn sure, #metoo is never a statistic she falls under. 
while i do not support how i was treated back then, i am thankful that through my darkness, i eventually saw the light. i am proud of the woman i am and i am grateful for my journey and the people who, unconditionally, loved me through it.

text:
last year i interviewed ugandan-rwandan model @iamjudithheard about her nude pictures being leaked online - and being arrested for it. she was anxious about the publication of the cnn article (when her photos first came out she endured a barrage of online abuse) but when it came out she decided she wanted to tell her story in full with the help of @sophierhemery and me.

judith's experiences, from controlling partners to sexual abuse, are sadly shared with many women in africa and around the world. the fact that she is famous does not make her story any more important than the stories of other women, but it does have the potential to bring about change. our hope is that women and girls in uganda, east africa and elsewhere will read this piece, and the fact that 'judith heard said it' will make it easier for them to talk more openly about abuse - and to show solidarity with one another.

gillette's new #bullying and #metoo focused publicity campaign launched yesterday, faced blacklash for attacking men. intelligencer's josh barro comparing it with nike's cole kaepernick advert, writes "the difference in reaction to the two campaigns helps us see what kind of social changes companies will and won't be successful at pushing. nike's message to costumers is uplifting rather than accusatory. the gillette campaign is a downer, asking costumers to reflect on and changing their own behavior."

text:
(swipe)

source: the guardian and twitter

context: it’s only been 3 days since gillette released its advert on youtube yet it has already received 652,000 dislikes and countless mixed response from the public. 
in the advert, the voiceover asks, “is this the best a man can get?” as there are mentions of the #metoo movement and bullying and sexual harassment is shown. then, there are scenes where men intervene to end fights between boys and call out sexual harassment.

those against the advert have announced on social media that they will be boycotting gillette, despite using their products for years. many believe the video suggests the majority of men are violent thugs or sexually harass people. tv presenter piers morgan claims the advert is a “pathetic global assault on masculinity”. on the flip side, people who like the advert claim that it was necessary and conveyed a good, strong message. in bernice king’s opinion “this commercial isn’t anti-male. it’s pro-humanity,” whilst pr expert mark borkowski said “masculinity is a huge part of gillette’s brand, and there is recognition in this ad that the new generation is reworking that concept of masculinity and it is no longer the cliché it once was.” #toxic #masculinity #gillette #gilletteadvert #boycott #its #controversial #apparently #praise #abuse #men #human #decency #feminism #feminist #new #post #2019

text:
gillette crea controversia en las redes🤔😮
.
luego de 30 años, gillette revivió el eslogan de su antigua campaña de los 80’s pero con una aproximación totalmente distinta y controversial.
.
en la nueva campaña, la empresa desvirtúa su propia concepción del hombre de hace tres décadas generando críticas en todas las redes.
.
en el inicio del spot se puede escuchar noticas referentes al movimiento #metoo y el acoso sexual, y se suelta la pregunta ¿esto es lo mejor que el hombre puede ser? luego aparece un corto lapso de su anterior comercial que es roto por unos niños que corren el papel en el que es proyectado.
.
va cerrando la campaña con varias imágenes de situaciones machistas en la televisión con una voz en off que dice “creemos en lo mejor de los hombres: decir lo correcto, actuar de la manera correcta”.
.
en una declaración difundida en su sitio web, gillette, propiedad de p&g, afirma que tras la ola de denuncias de agresión y acoso sexual que ha sacudido a estados unidos y ha tenido ecos en otras partes del mundo, muchos hombres se sienten atrapados "entre el pasado y una nueva era de masculinidad".
.
como se puede observar, los números en youtube hablan por sí solos: a 260,000 personas le gusta el video y a 638,000 no. 
en twitter no se puede medir los "no me gusta", pero los comentarios no son positivos a pesar de que el audiovisual ha sido reproducido más de 12 millones de veces y acumula más de 200,000 likes.
.
la mayoría de los comentarios apuntan a que gillette, en su búsqueda de reorientar su perfil, echó mano de estereotipos masculinos y, de hecho, son los hombres, su principal objetivo de mercado, los que más se han sentido ofendidos.
.
estaremos atentos a la próxima movida de gillette para ver cómo trata de superar esta lucha quijotesca a través de las redes, que examinando las cifras parece un gran fracaso.

text:
#gillette has released a video ad campaign in conjunction with the #boysandgirlsclubsofamerica titled, #thebestmancanbe, playing off their original tagline launched 30 years ago, “the best a man can get." the campaign was created to challenge the very meaning of masculinity in 2019. the center of the ad's message revolves around taking corrective measures to stop toxic masculinity, and the negative image and abuse associated with the male gender, from transferring to the younger generation. to make this a reality, gillette vows to distribute $1m per year for the next 3 years to non-profit organizations executing the most interesting and impactful programs designed to help men of all ages achieve their personal best.
.
as expected, the video has garnered mixed reactions from the public. while the brand has received commendation from new supporters, there has also been a fair amount of backlash and withdrawal from long-time brand loyalists. some people are even questioning their motives.
.
#laundrites, what do you think of the ad? is this something that absolutely needed to be addressed? (we think so.) [full video linked in our instagram story.] #metoo #instylemagazine

text:
from @thesavoyshow -  damn, a #church member fully exposes a #bishop at her own church for raping dozens of #girls at their church including his own daughter. gave full address , names, dates and everything 👀 .. update: the man named in the video #mathewgibson is reportedly in custody. 
sorry sis. i have additional (here's a kleenex).
first all i have multiple issues with this video. the first being how she hijacked someone else's trauma and publicized it with reckless abandon. 
she named the pastor then identified all the victims. what gives her the right? and how does one belong to a church with babies popping up pregnant and none of the elder women know why until he's arrested. i'm not comfortable with the plausible deniability of our matriarchs and how some of them use histrionics to deflect from questions being asked regarding the welfare of the girls around them. 
and yes. the pastor is a monster, but i bet if you would have tried to tell any of them a year ago they'd system destroy your reputation. we're good at ignoring things then giving a tear jerking ugly cry for social media. but protecting these kids? not so much. i may be cynical but sometimes people just want attention for other people's pain.

text:
drew’s face = my thoughts about waking up at 3am and not being able to fall back asleep, followed by his 4:45am wakeup! ☹️😴
.
oh sweet boy, i get it! #metoo
.
feeling weak, tired, slow — i could have been frustrated with how hard it was or i could be grateful it was only 20 minutes and choose to accept i gave it my best today & encourage my team and my virtual fit club to do the same! 👭
.
every one of my wellness warriors is busy, going through something & the other thing we have in common is that we’re on the same journey — working on becoming stronger mind & body, at our own pace. 💪🏼 🧠 ❤️ .
it’s more than a business or a team, it’s a community — and one that i am so grateful to be a part of! 👯‍♀️
.
i know a lot of you don’t feel strong, you feel like you can’t do it, but i want you to know you are stronger than your excuses! 
you can do {and have done #thinkaboutit} hard things, friend! 💖

text:
surviving abuse and r. kelly

i refuse to watch the r. kelly docu-series on lifetime. nah, i’m good on that. i know it’s gonna have me all up in my feelings. plus, i’m a survivor of abuse and because of that, my perspective is a little different. to me, it’s not all about the abuser. i don’t even think about the man who abused me. i do, however, think about how my family could allow that to happen to me. i’m not gonna lie, it took me a lot of prayer and meditation to forgive everyone involved. in the end, it’s the parents and family who are responsible for making sure that nothing happens to their children. i saw some snippets of “surviving r. kelly” online and it seemed to me that the parents were willing to pawn their children off on r. kelly, a known child molester, for the chance to get rich-- that’s horrible.

it surprised me but i’ve also seen a lot of women commenting on social media about the series, saying that we should not tear down this black man and suggesting that the young women r. kelly took advantage of were ready and willing. that’s crazy! even if those girls were dressed sexy, they are still girls and he’s a grown man. he’s the one who should have behaved himself.

i mean, how many times have you heard your family (or a family you know) say something about avoiding a bad uncle? things like, “don’t get too close to uncle larry,” or “don’t sit on his lap at the bbq”-- this is part of the problem. we shouldn’t be telling our little girls to stay away from uncle larry, we should be telling uncle larry to stay away from the bbq. we have to better as a people to help stop predators-- even if they are in our family. 
tips to grow:

don’t leave your kids with everybody. be very careful who you leave your kids with. even if they aren’t abused they could pick up on the negative energy of whoever you decide to leave them with. be selective.

communicate with your kids about physical boundaries. no, they actually don’t need to be taught to hug everyone in the community. and talk to them about what is appropriate touching by an adult and what isn't.

seek help and healing when needed. therapy can help. supposedly r. kelly was molested as a child and perha

text: for today’s takeover, we’re talking about backlash that people face when they report against sexual violence. dr. christine blasey ford was in the center of the news in 2018 for coming forward about her sexual assault allegation against judge brett kavanaugh. she was brave enough to come forward during the time so the country would be aware of the person who would possibly be appointed as a new supreme court justice. as a result, she had to relive her experience through the trail as well as deal with the backlash from the public who supported kavanaugh. dr. blasey ford was a target to harassment and death threats, forced to relocate from her home, and had her email hacked among other horrible acts. author of glamour’s article “death threats and discrediting” abby gardner writes “while blasey ford is the one actually under the attack of credible death threats and violent vitriol, kavanaugh is the person with all the protections of the government.” [dr. christine blasey ford]. #christineblaseyford #metoo

text:
this wednesday my woman crush is none other than, @michelinepitt 😍
 in december this beauty queen made a stop at @bestdresseddame (amazing pinup/rockabilly shop in jacksonville) for the day! i popped by to meet her and it meant the world to me. her clothing line @vixen_by_micheline_pitt knows how to make a girl make an entrance at any occasion. but on top of creating one of the most beloved and dynamic fashion lines in the pinup world, she's a heroine. micheline pitt has bravely worked with @rainn to produce a promo to speak about what she's had to overcome. i too have had to grow past my own darkness. last year was my 10 year survivor anniversary, it's been a decade since i was sexually assaulted. if you would've told me at 16 where i would be now, alive and smiling, i would'nt have believed you. i've come a long way and meeting micheline showed me that the sky's the limit. the attack may have changed me but i won't let it stop me. i will be strong for myself and for the men, women, and children that do not know if they can live another day. dear survivor, your life is worth living, so do so most undauntedly. and ladies, you are a "vixen not a victim", always keep that in your heart. thank you, micheline, for being such a light, you reminded me to be fearless and chase my dreams. 💞

text:
this book was the reason that we fell in love with usborne. it came in our starter kit and i literally read this book every single day for weeks to my daughter. she just loved all the things to discover and got so excited every time we read it. this is her telling me to “shh” because she was “reading” 😍😍📚
the very first book of things to spot , along with many other amazing titles are in this kit sale that i’m sure you keep hearing about 💕
this little venture did amazing things not only for my children, but for me as well. i was raising my two little ones and was feeling a little disjointed from the outside world. usborne gave me a sense of purpose outside of “mom”. it sparked my creativity, encouraged me to get outside of my bubble, and i was able to build friendships with so many other moms feeling the same way i was feeling. i wasn’t alone anymore. and you don’t have to feel that way either. ❤️❤️
if you are in the least bit curious, don’t be afraid to reach out to me, even just to chat about your day! sometimes that’s all it takes to feel a bit better. .
.
.

text:
last year, we heard from so many women, including those in our preemptive love community, who bravely shared their experience with sexual assault. at the same time, on a large-scale political level, there was combative debate around phrases like "believe women" and the importance and value of the #metoo movement. ⠀
⠀
today, we press in closer. we ask “what if someone i know personally, work with, or love shares with me their experience of sexual assault? how do i show up with love and compassion? how can i be a force of healing in that moment of vulnerability?”⠀
⠀
preemptive love staff-member, sexual assault nurse, and war veteran @dianaoestreich offers us a way forward. use the link in our bio to read more.⠀
⠀
(https://lovefir.st/2fvq6he)
name: Preemptive Love Coalition

⠀
today, we press in closer. we ask “what if someone i know personally, work with, or love shares with me their experience of sexual assault? how do i show up with love and compassion? how can i be a force of healing in that moment of vulnerability?”⠀
⠀
preemptive love staff-member, sexual assault nurse, and war veteran @dianaoestreich offers us a way forward. use the link in our bio to read more.⠀
⠀
(https://lovefir.st/2fvq6he)

text:
recent @tedxpasadena speakers discuss a father-daughter’s ‘framework of healing’ in public conversation series 
american book award-winning author of @blackmanofhappiness joins daughter and united shades of america executive producer in creative exchange on january 20 at red stories 
los angeles – 
in the charged era of #metoo, a courageous father and daughter will discuss how they created a personal ‘framework of healing’ during 15 years of working together after convicting and jailing her predator ex-stepfather, as featured guests of  @jaha0903 presents: red stories-long beach public conversation series on january 20, 2019, 6pm, at cirevellos, 4115 n. viking way, long beach, ca 90808. tickets cost $10 in advance and $15 at the door and can be purchased by clicking the link in my bio. 
the talk by award-winning author peter j. harris and adenike a. harris builds on themes that were the subject of their recent tedxpasadena talk. 
for red stories, ‘pops’nade’ will be joined by dr. donny jackson, clinical psychologist, veteran poet, and emmy-winning executive producer of cnn’s documentary series, united shades of america with w. kamau bell. @scriptdoctord 
photo by @rrandalphotos 
ticket link in bio: red stories

the talk by award-winning author peter j. harris and adenike a. harris builds on themes that were the subject of their recent tedxpasadena talk. 
for red stories, ‘pops’nade’ will be joined by dr. donny jackson, clinical psychologist, veteran poet, and emmy-winning executive producer of cnn’s documentary series, united shades of america with w. kamau bell.

#repost @brookespoetry (@get_repost)

join us for this exciting reading featuring three award-winning poets: james arthur, gale burns, and natalie whittaker! tickets are free, but places are limited. please register at the eventbrite link: https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/james-arthur-gale-burns-natalie-whittaker-poetry-reading-tickets-54951235625

james arthur was born in connecticut and grew up in canada. he is the author of the poetry collection the suicide's son, forthcoming in spring 2019 from véhicule press. his debut, charms against lightning, is available from copper canyon press. his chapbook hundred acre wood was published in 2018 by anstruther press. find out more about james here: http://www.jamesarthurpoetry.com

gale burns is a london-based prizewinning poet who is a writer-in-residence at both the sydenham arts festival and kingston university, where he teaches creative writing. he convenes the long-running shuffle poetry series in london, and was a 2012 hawthornden fellow. he is widely published with three pamphlets and a collection just out from eyewear entitled mute house: https://www.galeburns.co.uk

natalie whittaker is from south east london, where she works as a secondary school teacher. her poems have been published in poetry news, brittle star, aesthetica creative writing annual, #metoo: a women’s poetry anthology and south bank poetry. natalie was awarded second place in the poetry on the lake short poem competition 2018 and the oxford brookes international poetry competition 2017. her debut pamphlet from ignitionpress is called shadow dogs: https://www.brookes.ac.uk/poetry-centre/ignition-press/poets/ #poetry #oxford #poetrycommunity

text: new packaging but same old tricks from this advert. brands have been telling people how to behave since day one. essentially, that you must align yourself with the image we present to you in order to be attractive and acceptable, and buying our product will aid in that alignment. now that the collective conversation post #metoo is concerning so called “toxic masculinity”, gillette have decided it is their duty to dictate what a “good” man should be. the fact that we find ourselves in a society where the most prominent ethical and moral guidance is coming from the mouthpiece of the corporation is worrying to say the least. how did we find ourselves in this swamp of agenda driven, didactic pseudo-morality. the corporations want your money!!!!! this crass virtue signalling is a farce. regardless of where you stand in the current uneasy gender relations debate, the corporations should not be the ones that provide us with moral guidance. that society is bereft of any kind of moral leadership just goes to show how adrift we have become, how severed we are from any solid ground. and in our detached state, we are at our most vulnerable to advertising’s effects. #gillette #capitalism #advertising #stupidadvertising #advertisingisstupid #corporation #morality

text:
last week i did a 20 year #flashback post commemorating going back to school after two decades, before this #10yearchallenge was a thing. but this ties into another post i'm working on that ties up the energy of the past 10 years as we look ahead to the energetic influences of the next decade. ✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨
in 2009, i was still reeling from the murders my ex-husband committed during a july 4th, 2008 quadruple #homicide. my hair was growing out again after chopping it all off to disguise my identity when i had to go into hiding in 2007. the next decade would be one of tremendous healing. 💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛💛

text:
washington - thousands of requests by men to bring in child and adolescent brides to live in the united states were approved over the past decade, according to government data obtained by the associated press. in one case, a 49-year-old man applied for admission for a 15-year-old girl.

the approvals are legal: the immigration and nationality act does not set minimum age requirements for the person making the request or for that person's spouse or fiancee. by contrast, to bring in a parent from overseas, a petitioner has to be at least 21 years old.... read the rest on abc7chicago.com or any other news outlet using google. we need to talk about real immigration issues like this not a wall that won’t work! why is legal ?????

text:
this is how a *real* man should look at you. this man. my hubs. coming in hot this week with the defend-his-fiery-wife win.

i chose this picture for this post because it makes me feel strong, beautiful, and super f*ing loved. everything my assaulter was looking to diminish.

this past week tanner and i went to a show with a few friends, and at said show i was assaulted. at first the guy was just aggressively “flirting”. then he grabbed me inappropriately. when i told him to back off, he grabbed me again. when i shoved him away from me he took a swing. when my girlfriend intervened, he took a swing at her. for those of you who know me, you know i’m not one to back down, it can be a fault of mine. sometimes my fieriness can flare up when it isn’t warranted. this was not this night, this was a man who needed to be stopped and put in his place. said man-child escalated things, attempted to assault me further, and found himself in a cell.

tanner isn’t one for confrontation, but this was different, i was defending myself. and for every piece of scum who thinks it’s ok to lay a hand on anyone, none-the-less a woman, there are five men there to put him in his place. tanner wasn’t alone in coming to defense, and a good friend made sure to make his mark as well. but to all the strangers who stepped up and made sure my attacker knew he wasn’t going home unscathed, thank you.

as for the man-child, i’ll see you in court.

this past week tanner and i went to a show with a few friends, and at said show i was assaulted. at first the guy was just aggressively “fliing”. then he grabbed me inappropriately. when i told him to back off, he grabbed me again. when i shoved him away from me he took a swing. when my girlfriend intervened, he took a swing at her. for those of you who know me, you know i’m not one to back down, it can be a fault of mine. sometimes my fieriness can flare up when it isn’t warranted. this was not this night, this was a man who needed to be stopped and put in his place. said man-child escalated things, attempted to assault me fuher, and found himself in a cell.

tanner isn’t one for confrontation, but this was different, i was defending myself. and for every piece of scum who thinks it’s ok to lay a hand on anyone, none-the-less a woman, there are five men there to put him in his place. tanner wasn’t alone in coming to defense, and a good friend made sure to make his mark as well. but to all the strangers who stepped up and made sure my attacker knew he wasn’t going home unscathed, thank you.

as for the man-child, i’ll see you in cou.

text:
i can see this storm will come back again and again. but everytime i endure, i learn. i figure out how i can cope with this terrible thing.
.
facing what happened to me; the lasting harm it's still causing, is so much more brutal than anything i've ever had to do.
.
and yet, even after the worst of it... i'm still here. i'm still standing. as long as i have that, i know it will get better. and that's everything right now.
.
.
.

text:
the response to this advert is really surprising. the ad highlights some of the things that some men do wrong - not all men, just some men. i'm surprised that so many men feel personally attacked - rather than stepping back and acknowledging that the issues raised are real. i don't understand how some men watch this and feel like they are the victim! it's similar to raising racism issues with a white person only for them to feel personally attacked and uncomfortable that you are talking about it.
.
it's also concerning that some people are so outraged about the tone of the ad but probably don't care less about the actual issues it's addressing. .
they irony is that alot of the people so outraged are probably the same people that accuse others of being too sensitive, 'pc' or snowflakes. yet they have massively over-reacted when some negative behaviours of men are highlighted.
.
what do you think? was the ad offensive? was it good? do you understand why people were outraged? .

text:
👊
@gillette: set a good example for your sons; they’re watching, and they’re learning from you. treat other with respect and be a mature grown up.

@activistmommyofficial, morphed into the shape of a chicken: this is disrespectful and condescending!

no one said masculinity is toxic; toxic masculinity, as shown in the ad, is harmful to dozens of demographics. my child, noriam, has autism and xe got bullied a lot for stimming, not being as athletic as other kids, and for enjoying cartoons. 
noriam has also been sexual harassed by straight cisgender men and women for being gender fluid.

text_retweet:
well said @rhysuhlich 👇🏻👇🏻💥 #repost @rhysuhlich
・・・
i feel a real longing to write about intimacy from a mens perspective. about the confusion of what actually drives us and our sexual desires..... about  the control, the shame and disfunction many men hold. the cheating, the prostitiutes, the porn... then the shame, then repeat..... i know for much of my life i’ve been completly confused (even addicted) to the idea of either using women as objects for gratification\control or purely connecting to them with on open heart..... ive learnt (after many trials) that opening your heart (more often than your fly) to the feminine is not giving up control or being weak, it’s the bravest thing a man can do..... and the most intimate. undoubtedly, i believe that men can have intimate connections purely with their hearts (with either gender, for that matter) that are just as satisfying on all levels as physical intimacy (especially if disfunctional) . for i think, deep down that’s what we as men are actually longing for..... yet somehow in this modern day or porn, fear driven male leadership, gender stereotypes (not to mention any prior abuse) it’s been completly fucked up and lost. for me, as much as it brings up fears of judgement.... writing about intimacy from a mens point of view..... about the dance between the masculine and feminine (whether physical or not) is something my soul is screaming at me to express.  photo by the ever beautiful soul @dorotheabarth

text:
the educational civil rights law title ix is open for notice and comment. i'm writing something every day to raise awareness about a problem it seeks to address: sexual violence. today's focus: campus sexual assault survivors who are men.

thanks to the invisibility of men as victims, research on their survival of campus sexual assault is dwarfed by research on women—but here’s what the small, but growing body of research shows: (1) 5-12% of college men who live on/near campus are sexually assaulted;
(2) college men 18-24 are 78% more likely to be sexual assaulted than their non-student peers; (3) rates of victimization are likely higher for college men who are also lgbtq, of color, and/or have a disability; research shows lifetime prevalence is consistently higher across these populations;
(4) 1/3 of college men who survive sexual assault don’t tell anyone;
(5) male students who are sexually assaulted before starting college are more likely to be victimized again during their time on campus.

dominant media narratives frame campus sexual assault solely around men (as assailants) versus women (as victims). this is harmful because it has a silencing effect on victims who are men. the most vulnerable survivors (trans, lower-income, of color, etc.) end up bearing the brunt of this narrow representation.

more than 90% of all college sexual assault victims don’t report.  being reported for committing sexual assault is extremely rare—and if it does happen, the chances of being found culpable and punished for it are comparable to harvard acceptance rates. we’re doing a disservice to ourselves to say "false accusations" should be men's only concern around title ix rights and gender-based violence.

when it comes to men and boys in education, the chances being targeted by a fabricated rape report is not the epidemic; surviving sexual violence in silence is. #titleix is about civil rights and male survivors deserve them, too. 
check out #linkinbio for sources and more info. stay tuned for tomorrow's installment!
.
.

name: Wagatwe Wanjuki
tweet_full:
the educational civil rights law title ix is open for notice and comment. i am writing something every day to raise awareness about a problem it seeks to address: sexual violence. today's focus: campus sexual assault survivors who are men.

thanks to the invisibility of men as victims, research on their survival of campus sexual assault is dwarfed by research on women—but here’s what the small, but growing body of research shows: (1) 5-12% of college men who live on/near campus are sexually assaulted;
(2) college men 18-24 are 78% more likely to be sexual assaulted than their non-student peers; (3) rates of victimization are likely higher for college men who are also lgbtq, of color, and/or have a disability; research shows lifetime prevalence is consistently higher across these populations;
(4) 1/3 of college men who survive sexual assault don’t tell anyone;
(5) male students who are sexually assaulted before starting college are more likely to be victimized again during their time on campus.

domit media narratives frame campus sexual assault solely around men (as assailants) versus women (as victims). this is harmful because it has a silencing effect on victims who are men. the most vulnerable survivors (trans, lower-income, of color, etc.) end up bearing the brunt of this narrow representation.

more than 90% of all college sexual assault victims don’t report.  being reported for committing sexual assault is extremely rare—and if it does happen, the chances of being found culpable and punished for it are comparable to harvard acceptance rates. we’re doing a disservice to ourselves to say "false accusations" should be men's only concern around title ix rights and gender-based violence.

when it comes to men and boys in education, the chances being targeted by a fabricated rape report is not the epidemic; surviving sexual violence in silence is. #titleix is about civil rights and male survivors deserve them, too. 
check out #linkinbio for sources and more info. stay tuned for tomorrow's installment!
.
.
.
.
#twetalks #tweblogs #academiatoo #metoocampus #stopbetsy #savetitleix #handsoffix #titleixresearch

 de 13:00 a 16:59
 de 17:00 a 20:59 horas
estos periodos coinciden con las horas habituales de entrada y salida del trabajo y la escuela.

text:
kada sam videla reklamu za seriju "13 reasons why", pomislila sam da je u pitanju jos jedna tinejdzerska serija koja se vrti oko istih tema. medjutim, nakon odgledane dve sezone, drago mi je da je konacno snimljeno nesto fokusirano na ozbiljne probleme, kao sto su samoubistvo i zlostavljanje,  koje nase drustvo ima, a opet dovoljno zanimljivo adolescentima da nastave da gledaju. storyline je prilagodjen americkoj publici, ali u svakoj skoli, u svakoj zemlji, skoro svakoj devojci i zeni, desavaju se iste stvari, u manjoj ili vecoj meri. svaki roditelj bi trebalo ovo da odgleda, kao i svaki tinejdzer, jer ignorisanjem problema, on postaje samo veci. / when i first saw a commercial for the "13 reasons why" tv show, i thought it was another teenage series that was concentrated around same old topics. however, after watching two seasons, i am pleased that we finally have a tv show that has been focused on serious problems, such as suicide and sexual assault/abuse, which our society suffers from, and yet still interesting enough for adolescents to continue to watch. storyline is adapted to the american audience, but in every school, in every country, almost to every girl and woman, the same things happen, to a lesser or greater extent. each parent should watch this show, just like every teenager, because when we ignore the problem, the problem becomes only bigger. 
#aleksinzakon #metoomovement #metoo #stopbullying .

text:
las opiniones negativas han escalado en pocas horas a un intento de boicot en contra de la compañía de hojas de afeitar gillette.

y es que el nuevo anuncio de la compañía estadounidense que hace referencia al acoso, al movimiento #metoo y a la "masculinidad tóxica" generó una fuerte oposición, principalmente en redes sociales.

otros consideran que la campaña publicitaria tiene un mensaje positivo que hace un llamado a una redefinición de la masculinidad actual. 
el video se titula en inglés we believe (nosotros creemos) y con él que la compañía dice que quiere que los hombres se responsabilicen de sus acciones. "intimidación. acoso. ¿es esto lo mejor que un hombre puede lograr? solo al desafiarnos a nosotros mismos a hacer más podemos alcanzar lo mejor de nosotros. decir lo correcto, actuar de la manera correcta", dice la descripción del anuncio en youtube. @elmostrador_braga

text: backlash against the #metoo movement comes in many forms. one example is the #himtoo movement which was created by people who believed that the me too movement was a movement toward “victimization” and that the modern politics made it a “scary time for young men in america.” one group, save our sons, focuses on informing the public about legal cases against college men who have been acquitted of sexual misconduct. while false allegations are a possibility, it is our focus to make our community a space for trust. we should not be flooding the media with false cases when there are already so many people who do not feel safe enough to come forward about their own experiences. [first picture of a tweet from the mother of a navy vet who wrote: this is my son. he graduated #1 in boot camp. he was awarded the uso award. he was #1 in a school. he is a gentleman who respects women. he won’t go on solo dates due to the current climate of false sexual accusations by radicals feminists with an axe to grind. i vote. #himtoo second picture of his response tweet, that was my mom. sometimes the people we love do things that hurt us without realizing it. let’s turn this around. i respect and #believewomen i never have and never will support #himtoo i’m a proud navy vet, cat dad, and ally. also, twitter, your meme game is on point.]
name: WilliamsSAPR

text:
my life is about healing moving forward and using my past to help others. i wrote the words to this song when i was 19 from  a personal experience and now at 41 i finally put some music to it and damn that was good for my soul!! in the dark of the night
when it didn't feel right
when deep down inside
was a voice i couldn't hide
a part of my soul 
that would not be denied 
and god knows the truth
i never lied 
and he keeps on telling me
girl hold this one thing true
there will always be you 
yeah there will always be you
he can't take that away from you 
in the dark of the night
now i hang on tight 
i know the shadows
are cast out by the light 
i know some wrongs 
can never be made right
but i will hang on
yes now i will fight
girl hold this one thing true
there will always be you
there will always be you
he can't take that away from you -miranda mcnamara 
#recovery #metoo #originalmusic #songwriter

text: to all my lady beasts this one is for you, please read! i want to open up about something that is an issue over and over again, i see it happen to all of us but i never hear it talked about. gym can be intimidating yes, especially the weight room, but when men are creeping left and right, it makes me want to up and leave. 😔 i am struggling enough pushing myself to lift these weights, and i have to deal with a set of eyes scouring me while i’m doing it??!! no thank you. 🤬 i think for me the worst part is not being able to confront someone because i don’t want to create “conflict.” but thinking back on why i either politely say “thanks.” or don’t say anything, i’m wondering what’s “peace” when you’re not even comfortable in your own space? no matter what gender you identify as, we can all agree the best part about getting stronger is the empowerment you feel during a workout. how empowering does it feel when you’re constantly objectified?! 🥺 i’ve been told time and time again to refrain from saying anything as to not provoke tension or violence. but i’ve had enough and i’m so so so sick of staying complacent, especially when it’s happening at one of the places i love the most. i don’t have an exact solution as there is no exact solution to the #metoo movement other than making sure these conversations happen and happen often in order to create real change. @ men if you are reading this, please be mindful of your actions. i’m not trying to make anyone the bad guy here, i’m just asking for all women that we are granted the space and respect we deserve to blossom into our beautiful beast potentials 💪🏼 if you read all of this (ur a star and the only reason this account is alive lol) let me know your thoughts if you have em. i really do want to get the conversation going and offer each other support as to what to do in these kind of situations, and this goes beyond the gym for sure. sorry for all the #politics, i just wanted to voice my opinion about being peacefully respected in the gym. thanks for hearing me out 💜💜💜 @metoomvmt #metoo #fitness

text:
today witchy wednesday is woman wednesday and i’m thinking of doing this theme for awhile. the third women’s march is this saturday and i can’t believe i’m marching yet again. in the words of my 74-year-old aunt, “i never thought i’d have to march for women’s rights twice in my lifetime.”
👩🏻👩🏻‍🦰👩🏽‍🦱👩🏼‍🦳👵🏼👱🏼‍♀️🧑🏻🧕🏻👩🏻‍💼👩🏼‍🔧👩🏼‍⚖️👧🏻
i’m posting these statistics about sexual assault and rape because it is still a problem in this country. women are still getting blamed and “prevention” seems to be that we need to watch what we wear, watch what we drink and how much, watch where we go. the problem is not women. the problem is rapists and sexual predators. as a young girl of 14, the person who abused me lived in the same house. i was not dressed provocatively, drinking or partying in my own house at 14.
🙄
the patriarchy must end. boys need to be taught how to be gentlemen and not rapists. the legal system needs to be more harsh and stop treating this as an “atta boy” secret society.
⚖️
as a tarot card reader who specializes in love and relationships, one of the main reasons relationships are suffering is because of sexual abuse. this needs to stop!
.
.
.
.
#womenwednesday #women #rape #sexualassault #sexualabuse #iamasurvivor #metoo #enoughisenough #rapeculture #rapecultureisreal #rapeawareness #smashthepatriarchy #sexualassaultawareness #sexualassaultsurvivor #sexualassaultprevention #endsexualassault #stopsexualassault #womenempowerment

text:
the power of the female.  even in the vedic texts, there is a distinction of female and male. no matter how much our society tries to change the fundamentals of human nature, even the ancient seers knew that there is a difference. yes, we are all created from male and female energies.  however, in vedic astrology, moon and venus are female planets.  moon (chandra ma in sanskrit) shows the emotional mind, and our maternal instinct.  the moon is always luminous somewhere in our sky.  that luminous light means that the female energy can tirelessly care for others and loved ones, around the clock.  in addition, it has implications for our minds as well.  indeed, the latin-derived word “lunacy” reflects that madness to be an effect of the moon.  the female energy have the power to make peace, and to sustain the human (and animal) population.  in addition, this power is strong enough to fix the emotional pains/sorrows of the world, even by touch.  also, venus (shukra) is female.  venus is the goddess of love, wife, beauty, art, sex, and passion.  and the highest form of love is called bhakti yoga, which is the unconditional and selfless love for the divine.  strong female energies are found in deities across the world such as aphrodite, hera, selene, kali, durga, varuni, ashi, sophia. 
#love #vedicastrology  #venus #chandra #vedicmoon #nycastrology #nyc  #nycspirituality #hinduism #vedanta #indians #vedas #nycmeditation #gita #lovelost #loveandloved #parasharahorashastra #shukra #sanskrit #wedding #marriage #indianweddings #southasianbridemagazine #greekmythology #durga #aphrodite #goddess #girlpower #metoo #feminism

text:
they “hate girls”? 😳

this is a copy of a casting call for a home depot commercial. the advertising agency is casting a 4 or 5-year-old boy who “hates girls” for a principal role. the commercial shot early jan 2019.

a formal letter was sent to the ceo of home depot on dec 24th, 2018. we asked him to reconsider broadcasting a commercial of a 4 or 5-year-old boy who “hates girls”. it’s been 3 weeks and we still haven’t heard back from him.

if you want to help us encourage home depot to evolve past outdated clichés then please support our efforts by commenting and sharing with all your friends. 
#changetheworld #stopthehate #homedepot #thebestmencanbe #metoo #sagaftra #craigmenear

text:
gillette recently released a commercial, “boys will be boys,” addressing the #metoo movement.⠀
📺⠀
it calls men to something better than misogyny, bullying, sexual harassment, and the objectifying of #women. it encourages men to use their strength and influence to protect the weak, to treat other human beings with dignity and value, and to hold one another accountable. it admits that not all men are bullies and misogynists, and it praises the virtuous acts of those doing the right things.⠀
🙌🏽⠀
nevertheless, the ad has generated a conflicted response from the public. one popular critique doesn't sit well with me. (link in profile.)⠀
😡 ⠀

text:
“शशशशश..!!! किसी से कुछ मत कहना, यह तुम्हारे और मेरे बीच की बात है, सीक्रेट है हमारा ।”
.
.
.
कमरे में घुसते ही उन्होने दरवाज़े की कुंडी लगा दी। आज पहले जैसी बात नही थी क्योंकि आज मुझे पता था कि अब क्या होगा। महज पाँच साल होगी उम्र मेरी जब अंकल मुझे पहली बार कमरे में लेकर गए थे। मेरे फेवरेट अंकल, और मेरा फेवरेट कमरा। आखिर क्यों न होता , इस कमरे में वो सब था जो एक पाँच साल के बच्चे को चाहिए होता है, खिलौने, टॉफ़ी, चॉकलेट, कॉमिक्स, वीडियो गेम्स। पर आज उस कमरे में वो सब नही था। थे तो बस अंकल और मैं। बन्द दरवाज़े के पीछे क्या होता है, यह किसी को कहा पता होता है। उस दिन मेरी गर्मियों की छुट्टी का पहला दिन था। नानी नाना मम्मी पापा सब बाहर बैठ बातें कर रहे थे कि इतने में अंकल मुझे खेलने के बहाने अपने कमरे में ले गए। क्या दिन था वो, क्या नज़ारा। अंकल और मुझे दोनो को जैसे जन्नत मिल गयी हो, मुझे उस कमरे में पड़े खिलौनो मे और उन्हें मेरे बदन में। जैसे जैसे मेरा हाथ खिलौना पर पड़ता रहा, उनका हाथ मेरे बदन को छूता रहा। गर्मियों के दिन थे, बदन पर पसीना था, अंकल के हाथ काफी ठंडे थे। मेरे बालो को सहला कर उन्होंने मेरे गालो को अपनी उंगलियों से छूना शुरू किया। "गर्मी है ना, पसीना पोंछ देता हूँ तेरा", उन्होंने धीरे से अपने मुँह से हवा मेरे चेहरे पर छोड़ते हुए कहा। जैसे गरम चाय का कप हमारे सामने होता है और हमसे रुका नही जाता और हम उसको ठंडा करने के लिए फूंक मारते रहते है, बस उस दिन अंकल ने मुझे अपना चाय का कप बना दिया था। जैसे जैसे वो मेरे बदन को छूते जा रहे थे, ज़ोर ज़ोर से फूंक मारे जा रहे थे। मुझे बड़ा ही मज़ा आ रहा था। "अंकल , आप कितने अच्छे हो, आपको खुद इतना पसीना आ रहा है फिर भी आप मेरे बदन से पसीना पोंछ मुझे फूंक मारे जा रहे हो", यह कहते ही मैन उनके गाल पर उन्हे चूम लिया। 5 साल का बच्चा और कर भी क्या सकता है। वो दोपहर पूरे दो घंटे तक अंकल की उँगलियों नें मेरे बदन के हर कोने को टटोला। अंकल ने मुझे अपनी गोद में और ऊपर कर के बिठा लिया। कुछ चुभ रहा था मुझे पर अंकल ने मुझे वहाँ बैठे रहने को कहा। सोचो, यह बात पढ़ने में आपको जितनी अजीब लग रही होगी तो लिखते हुए कैसे मेरे रोंगटे खड़े हुए होंगे। बस, एक वो दिन था और उसके आगे आने वाले साल, जो मेरी हमेशा नाना नानी के घर जाने की जिद होती थी। .
.

कमरे में घुसते ही उन्होने दरवाज़े की कुंडी लगा दी। आज पहले जैसी बात नही थी क्योंकि आज मुझे पता था कि अब क्या होगा। महज पाँच साल होगी उम्र मेरी जब अंकल मुझे पहली बार कमरे में लेकर गए थे। मेरे फेवरेट अंकल, और मेरा फेवरेट कमरा। आखिर क्यों न होता , इस कमरे में वो सब था जो एक पाँच साल के बच्चे को चाहिए होता है, खिलौने, टॉफ़ी, चॉकलेट, कॉमिक्स, वीडियो गेम्स। पर आज उस कमरे में वो सब नही था। थे तो बस अंकल और मैं। बन्द दरवाज़े के पीछे क्या होता है, यह किसी को कहा पता होता है। उस दिन मेरी गर्मियों की छुट्टी का पहला दिन था। नानी नाना मम्मी पापा सब बाहर बैठ बातें कर रहे थे कि इतने में अंकल मुझे खेलने के बहाने अपने कमरे में ले गए। क्या दिन था वो, क्या नज़ारा। अंकल और मुझे दोनो को जैसे जन्नत मिल गयी हो, मुझे उस कमरे में पड़े खिलौनो मे और उन्हें मेरे बदन में। जैसे जैसे मेरा हाथ खिलौना पर पड़ता रहा, उनका हाथ मेरे बदन को छूता रहा। गर्मियों के दिन थे, बदन पर पसीना था, अंकल के हाथ काफी ठंडे थे। मेरे बालो को सहला कर उन्होंने मेरे गालो को अपनी उंगलियों से छूना शुरू किया। "गर्मी है ना, पसीना पोंछ देता हूँ तेरा", उन्होंने धीरे से अपने मुँह से हवा मेरे चेहरे पर छोड़ते हुए कहा। जैसे गरम चाय का कप हमारे सामने होता है और हमसे रुका नही जाता और हम उसको ठंडा करने के लिए फूंक मारते रहते है, बस उस दिन अंकल ने मुझे अपना चाय का कप बना दिया था। जैसे जैसे वो मेरे बदन को छूते जा रहे थे, ज़ोर ज़ोर से फूंक मारे जा रहे थे। मुझे बड़ा ही मज़ा आ रहा था। "अंकल , आप कितने अच्छे हो, आपको खुद इतना पसीना आ रहा है फिर भी आप मेरे बदन से पसीना पोंछ मुझे फूंक मारे जा रहे हो", यह कहते ही मैन उनके गाल पर उन्हे चूम लिया। 5 साल का बच्चा और कर भी क्या सकता है। वो दोपहर पूरे दो घंटे तक अंकल की उँगलियों नें मेरे बदन के हर कोने को टटोला। अंकल ने मुझे अपनी गोद में और ऊपर कर के बिठा लिया। कुछ चुभ रहा था मुझे पर अंकल ने मुझे वहाँ बैठे रहने को कहा। सोचो, यह बात पढ़ने में आपको जितनी अजीब लग रही होगी तो लिखते हुए कैसे मेरे रोंगटे खड़े हुए होंगे। बस, एक वो दिन था और उसके आगे आने वाले साल, जो मेरी हमेशा नाना नानी के घर जाने की जिद होती थी। .
.
continued in comments ⬇⬇

बच्चे को चाहिए होता है , खिलौने , टॉफ़ी , चॉकलेट , कॉमिक्स , वीडियो गेम्स। पर आज उस कमरे में वो सब नही था। थे तो बस अंकल और मैं। बन्द दरवाज़े के पीछे क्या होता है , यह किसी को कहा पता होता है। उस दिन मेरी गर्मियों की छुट्टी का पहला दिन था। नानी नाना मम्मी पापा सब बाहर बैठ बातें कर रहे थे कि इतने में अंकल मुझे खेलने के बहाने अपने कमरे में ले गए। क्या दिन था वो , क्या नज़ारा। अंकल और मुझे दोनो को जैसे जन्नत मिल गयी हो , मुझे उस कमरे में पड़े खिलौनो मे और उन्हें मेरे बदन में। जैसे जैसे मेरा हाथ खिलौना पर पड़ता रहा , उनका हाथ मेरे बदन को छूता रहा। गर्मियों के दिन थे , बदन पर पसीना था , अंकल के हाथ काफी ठंडे थे। मेरे बालो को सहला कर उन्होंने मेरे गालो को अपनी उंगलियों से छूना शुरू किया।  गर्मी है ना , पसीना पोंछ देता हूँ तेरा  , उन्होंने धीरे से अपने मुँह से हवा मेरे चेहरे पर छोड़ते हुए कहा। जैसे गरम चाय का कप हमारे सामने होता है और हमसे रुका नही जाता और हम उसको ठंडा करने के लिए फूंक मारते रहते है , बस उस दिन अंकल ने मुझे अपना चाय का कप बना दिया था। जैसे जैसे वो मेरे बदन को छूते जा रहे थे , ज़ोर ज़ोर से फूंक मारे जा रहे थे। मुझे बड़ा ही मज़ा आ रहा था।  अंकल , आप कितने अच्छे हो , आपको खुद इतना पसीना आ रहा है फिर भी आप मेरे बदन से पसीना पोंछ मुझे फूंक मारे जा रहे हो  , यह कहते ही मैन उनके गाल पर उन्हे चूम लिया। 5 साल का बच्चा और कर भी क्या सकता है। वो दोपहर पूरे दो घंटे तक अंकल की उँगलियों नें मेरे बदन के हर कोने को टटोला। अंकल ने मुझे अपनी गोद में और ऊपर कर के बिठा लिया। कुछ चुभ रहा था मुझे पर अंकल ने मुझे वहाँ बैठे रहने को कहा। सोचो , यह बात पढ़ने में आपको जितनी अजीब लग रही होगी तो लिखते हुए कैसे मेरे रोंगटे खड़े हुए होंगे। बस , एक वो दिन था और उसके आगे आने वाले साल , जो मेरी हमेशा नाना नानी के घर जाने की जिद होती थी। . . continued comment ⬇⬇

🧚‍♂️.

🧚‍♂️
vivo e defendo a pluralidade e as diferenças, mas é necessário ficar claro que modelos de vida que ferem outras vidas não é diferença, é violência!".
🧚‍♂️

text:
➕ this is the year of forgiveness for me.

there’s a lot going on behind these big brown eyes. 
there’s been 20+ years of traumas, betrayals, hurts, loses, pain & suffering at the hands of others. sexual assaults at the hands of people i trusted. physical and emotional assaults from people i wish i never let into my life. 
you can carry these things with you for decades, and i’m at the stage in my life where i say no more. 🙅🏼‍♀️ no more am i going to allow the people that hurt me to have power over me. 
as i’m writing this the tragically hip are playing at the coffee shop i’m sitting in. if anyone understood the pain i’ve experienced in my life, it’s my sisters. and tamara may be gone from earth, but she’s always with me. even sitting here she speaks to me through the radio, a comforting song by her favorite band, like a hug from heaven from my sister. 😇 
i don’t share these things publicly- ever. i’ve never talked on my page about being raped before. i watched from the sidelines as the #metoo movement started last year, and i just wasn’t strong enough to admit that that was me too... i worked hard on suppressing the trauma, putting it neatly in a box and hiding it away in the back of my brain. 
we all know how well that works right? it would insidiously come back to haunt me in the worst possible ways, at the worst possible times. 
for a long time i felt broken, damaged even. my relationships struggled from it. i choose one bad relationship after the next, seeking love in all the wrong men. 
i realize now that i’m not broken, i am not damaged. only an incredibly strong person could go through all i’ve been through and still be here pushing onwards towards success. 
so many people turn to alcohol or drugs to numb the pain of their past, i lost my sister to drugs because she had been hurt so much but she couldn’t recover. 
i want anyone reading this to know that you are strong. there is a better way to deal with your hurt and trauma. counselling, therapy, cbt, meditation, personal growth and self-help books have all helped me immensely. 
continued in comments...

text:
city officials and the police show up at r. kelly’s studio, but not for his arrest. 
chicago police are still looking for some sort of evidence in order to prosecute r. kelly, but they’ve yet to be successful. however, they might be inching closer. in surviving r. kelly, the singer was accused of using his recording studio to house alleged sex slaves. police and city officials surrounded the industrial warehouse in order to determine whether it was being used as a residence.

according to tmz, chicago pd pulled up to r. kelly’s recording studio in the westside of chicago earlier today with the cook county building and zoning department. however, it wasn’t due to the allegations made in surviving r. kelly. the building and zoning department’s only reason for being there is because the building is strictly meant for industrial purposes. police typically enter buildings with the building and zoning department for issues like this. the publication indicates they didn’t just enter his home because it’s r. kelly and the controversy surrounding his name.

kellz is actually facing eviction from the studio because he owes $166k in rent which is due at the end of the month or else he gets booted. many people believed that the police were at the building in order to arrest r. kelly, but that wasn’t the case. since the docuseries aired, there have been protestors outside of the studio in support of the #muterkelly movement. peep the video footage in the full story at www.itskenbarbie.com or swipe #rkelly #robertkelly #survivingrkelly #muterkelly #trappedinthecloset #lifetimetv #metoo #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #gossip

text_retweet:
repost from @taprootdoula on instagram: “birth in the u.s needs a #metoo. • as an experienced nurse i have witnessed each and every one of…” using @repostregramapp - birth in the u.s needs a #metoo.
•
as an experienced nurse i have witnessed each and every one of these things. i have intervened and i have not. i have reported these behaviors and i have not. i have called attention to these behaviors in my peers and i have not.
•
how can we discuss #metoo without discussing obstetrical violence? what is obstetrical violence? how overt or subtle is it? how widespread?
•
i speak bout birthing justice, implicit bias, #blackbirthmatters, and about obstetrical violence - because i’ve witnessed it. we need a change before we can hope to see an improvement. ever since i began nursing, i’ve watched care providers (nurses, midwives and doctors) pass the buck. i have, too. we minimize physical and emotional trauma and we aren’t accountable for our role. we can provide excellent, safe care while ensuring birthing people’s rights and humanity. in fact, we cannot keep them safe, unless we do. •
slide: @birthmonopoly via @earthsnaturaltouch

text:
apollo, god of light, a spirit of both healing and hunting radiates power gained through the absorption of others. a glowing sponge with prophetic vision who is considered the unblinking, all-seeing “eye of the day”, he is a protector, remaining loyal to those he loves. while apollos glow is nourishing and healing, his brilliance can be blinding and destructive. the archetype of apollo has both light and shadow aspects at play which will can explored through the myth of his pursuit (and sexual assault/stalking) of daphne.
∆
∆
on my blog post i go into a lot more detail about this archetype, the story of this myth, the herb and essential oil connected to this archetype as well as it's links with the #metoo movement and patriarchy. i will be posting in february 2019 a sequel article delving more deeply into patriarchy linkage with the symbol of the sun.
∆
∆
∆
* i love to burn dried basil instead of sage as a way to both not over use and abuse the production of sage as there is overproduction of this resource and as part of the #changemakerrising movement started by @gabriela_for_change i am trying to heighten my awareness and help our planet. so you can burn other herbs besides sage for the welfare of these herbs in our world as well as switch it up to help tune into the archetype of sun and apollo. ∆
∆
∆

text:
manifestación 15e - ni un paso atrás - puerta del sol
¿que qué es el feminismo para mí? el feminismo es esa forma de entender el mundo que apareció un día en mi cabeza, y que muy poco a poco fue creciendo en ella hasta cambiarlo todo.
no solo me abrió los ojos, me hizo volver a creer en mí misma y así salir de una relación de maltrato. gracias por despertarme antes de que fuese demasiado tarde. 
ojalá con gestos como la mani de ayer, y las que vendrán, cada vez haya más mujeres despertando y recuperando el control de sus vidas.
os quiero a todas vivas, y viviendo. 
#feminismo #madrid #metoo #sororidad #niunpasoatras #kaleborrokafeminista #preparandoel8m #loquecuestasoltarestascosasyloimportantequeesvisibilizarlas

text:
“but i’m scared”

these words can be a sword.

on one side, if you allow them, they will cut through you, and shrink your attempts at expansion with self-doubt, shame and connections to what hasn’t worked in the past.

on the other edge, swift action allows you to see through your fears, enabling what once petrified you frozen to break free and find liberation.

like a butterfly dissolving itself and transforming for flight, growth can be painful, scary, unfamiliar and uncomfortable.

it’s exactly this process in which courage is made.

and courage — the courage the be born, to speak up, to walk your path, to walk away, to find your truth is by very definition done so with discomfort.

there’s nothing wrong with being afraid and awkward. a reminder that if you’re feeling that way it comes to your dreams right now, keep going: it will be worth it

text:
“hey, that’s not how we treat each other.”⠀
.⠀
gillette is getting some praise and some push-back from their new commercial. personally, i think it’s a step in the right direction. they are trying to acknowledge that masculinity is complex, and with the #metoo movement the definition of what it is to “be a man” is changing. i commend their efforts. not only did they make this commercial, they are committing to challenge the stereotype of what a man is in their advertisements. they have also committed to donate a million dollars per year for the next three years to organizations that support and promote healthy masculinity. first year, the boys and girls club.⠀
.⠀
advertising matters. kids see these images and commercials and emulate what they think they’re seeing. tv commercials and advertisements have effects on the psyche – that’s why advertising works. healthier images do a make a difference, and i commend gillette for the change.⠀
.⠀
here’s the link: https://buff.ly/2srzpk1⠀
.⠀
#gillette #thebestamancanget #sexliterate #healthymasculinity #sexfacts #sexeducation

text:
consentement et masculinité 
plusieurs hommes hétérosexuels se sentiraient personnellement attaqués par les standards changeants liés au consentement. plusieurs diraient qu’ils sentent que les lois les visent, leur donnant une responsabilité particulière que ne portent pas les femmes. en partie, c’est parce que statistiquement parlant, les hommes commettent la grande majorité de la violence sexuelle. et les choses qui sont nécessaires pour un vrai consentement sont les mêmes choses qui sont interdites par nos idées dominantes, toxiques de ce que cela signifie d’être un homme : le confort avec la vulnérabilité, la patience face au rejet, des habiletés de communication empreintes de compassion, et l’habileté à voir les femmes comme des collaboratrices égalitaires. 
some men feel personally attacked by changing consent standards. many tell me they feel the rules are targeting them, giving them special responsibility that women don’t bear. that’s not true, but i understand why they see it that way. in part it’s because statistically speaking, men commit the vast majority of sexual violence. so any conversations about healing our sexual culture require us to talk specifically about masculinity. and the very things required for a deep moral sexual consent practice are the things forbidden by our dominant, toxic ideas about what it means to be a man: comfort with vulnerability, patience with rejection, compassionate communication skills, and the ability to see women as co-equal collaborators. - inspiré de jaclyn friedman, auteure du texte « yes means yes: consent should be about morals, not laws »
#consent #masculinity #metoo #sexual #culture

text:
paul francis gadd (born 8 may 1944), known by the stage name gary glitter, is an english former glam rock singer who achieved popular success in the 1970s and 80s. he was known for his extreme glam image of glitter suits, make-up and platform boots, and his energetic live performances. he sold over 20 million records, spent 168 weeks on the uk singles chart and had 21 hit singles placing him in the top 100 uk most successful chart acts. from 1997, he returned to public notice for committing sex offences, being imprisoned for downloading child pornography in 1999, and child sexual abuse and attempted rape in 2006 and 2015. #themfirst
⬇️
according to the survey of inmates of state correctional facilities by the u.s. department of justice bureau of justice statistics. * those inmates who were convicted of committing violent acts against children were more like to have been white, a percentage of nearly 70%, than any other race. * white inmates were nearly three times more likely to have victimized a child than black inmates. ⬇️
according to rainn (rape, abuse and incest national network) and the bureau of justice, 57% of all sexual violence perpetrators are white males.
⬇️
according to suicide prevention expert, dr. christine moutier, white, middle-aged men account for 70% of deaths from suicide each year. nine-tenths of them are from a lower socioeconomic classthese are being called “deaths of despair.”harvard public policy professor robert d. putnam, told the bbc, "this is part of the larger emerging pattern of evidence of the links between poverty, hopelessness and health.” veterans are often one of the largest segments within this group. according to a 2014 veterans affairs (va) report, 20 commit suicide each day. 65% of them are age 50 or older. a larger segment of this group has chosen the slow suicide.

paul francis gadd (born 8 may 1944), known by the stage name gary glitter, is an english former glam rock singer who achieved popular success in the 1970s and 80s. he was known for his extreme glam image of glitter suits, make-up and platform boots, and his energetic live performances. he sold over 20 million records, spent 168 weeks on the uk singles chart and had 21 hit singles placing him in the top 100 uk most successful chart acts. from 1997, he returned to public notice for committing sex offences, being imprisoned for downloading child pornography in 1999, and child sexual abuse and attempted rape in 2006 and 2015. #themfirst
⬇️
according to the survey of inmates of state correctional facilities by the u.s. department of justice bureau of justice statistics. * those inmates who were convicted of committing violent acts against children were more like to have been white, a percentage of nearly 70%, than any other race. * white inmates were nearly three times more likely to have victimized a child than black inmates. ⬇️
according to rainn (rape, abuse and incest national network) and the bureau of justice, 57% of all sexual violence perpetrators are white males.
⬇️
according to suicide prevention expert, dr. christine moutier, white, middle-aged men account for 70% of deaths from suicide each year. nine-tenths of them are from a lower socioeconomic classthese are being called “deaths of despair.”harvard public policy professor robert d. putnam, told the bbc, "this is part of the larger emerging pattern of evidence of the links between poverty, hopelessness and health.” veterans are often one of the largest segments within this group. according to a 2014 veterans affairs (va) report, 20 commit suicide each day. 65% of them are age 50 or older. a larger segment of this group has chosen the slow suicide.

text:
gillete @gillette lanza campaña contra la masculinidad tóxica

un comercial de gillete es tendencia en las redes sociales, pero no por lo que vende sino por lo que dice. el anuncio “we believe” o “creemos” trata temas como la masculinidad tóxica, el acoso sexual y el movimiento #metoo. gillette juega con su famoso lema y pregunta: “¿es esto lo mejor que un hombre puede ser?” después, exhiben a hombres acosando a mujeres en la tv, un hombre minimizando la participación de una mujer y a niños golpeando a otros. el anunciante dice “no podemos seguir con las excusas viejas como la de que los niños son niños”. el comercial concluye con la siguiente frase: “porque los niños que están viendo serán los hombres del mañana”. gillette explicó, en su sitio web, que con este comercial busca reconocer el papel que tienen marcas como ellos, en la influencia de la cultura. “intimidación. acoso. ¿esto es lo mejor que un hombre puede conseguir? solo desafiándonos a nosotros mismos a hacer más podremos acercarnos a lo mejor de nosotros mismos. decir lo correcto, actuar de la manera correcta”, es uno de los mensajes que reza la marca en dicho anuncio.

el comercial desató todo tipo de comentarios por parte de los internautas, pues mientras unos creen que esta campaña es una tontería, hay quienes aplauden el atrevimiento de la marca.

reposted from @adamtghani➡️ " i consider this character and the one she played in #indecentproposal to be two of the most interesting female roles in 90s movies, particularly due to both films being an exploration of sex as power... with one subject to a man’s power and the other wielding her own over a man. i really am surprised no one brings up these films in the age of #metoo, as they were delving into these hot topic themes 25 years ago. to think, by the mid 90s, demi was only doing one film a year and if you consider the amount of scripts she was probably getting, it’s a credit to her that she would have such excellent instincts for what would be relevant all these years later"

text:
i want to post about some things in my feed for those who don't watch stories. i realized recently that as a victim of sexual assault, i have a choice to quietly handle it on my own, or to stand up and be an advocate. i am strong, and i have a voice, and i choosing to use it. i am choosing to use this platform, freely accessible to damn near everyone in this society, to hopefully enact some sort of change, even if it is only in the mindset of a few people. i will be regularly posting questions and opening up discussions about sexual assault, on my stories. i have made a "high light" titled sa advocacy. everything related to those topics will be added there. my inbox is open, my heart is open, i am here for you. i ask, please, even if you are not a victim, that you participate. if you are a friend of mine, if i have touched your life at all, please join in this discussion. 1 out of 3 women, and 1 out of 5 men, are victims of sexual assault or abuse. if you are not one, you know one. let's work on being better friends, family, partners, coworkers, loved ones, for victims, together. 📷 : @armaan.captures
#sexaulassault #victimadvocacy #metoo #metoomovement

text: im sorry but this video was actually awful. its not even the fact that i disagree with the message of the video (which is that all men are pigs and its time for men to stop being the pieces of shit that they naturally are so they can conform to the movement of #metoo and get rid of their so-called “toxic masculinity”) the big reason that this commercial was so bad was because @gillette was obviously pandering to political correctness in hopes of being percieved as “a good political voice” for the me too movement. i know people do bad things and sexual harassment is an issue. my mom worked a job and she got hit on by people who should’ve known better, there’s no words to say how mad that made me. one of my best friends worked a job for awhile and despite being only like 16 at the time she always had guys much older than her come in and say things to her that made her uncomfortable, and i wish i could’ve done something about it but i couldn’t. but even after all of that experience i don’t believe, (and i know that my mom and my friend don’t believe either) that men are toxic by default, or that being a man is bad. men shouldn’t be desensitized and be told by the media they aren’t allowed to do things that society perceives as “masculine.” boys should be allowed to wrestle. men should be allowed to have confidence. its not okay to be creepy and advancing, but thats common knowledge and real men don’t do that. we should be allowed to mess with each other and give each other crap. the message of this commercial is wrong. men aren’t animals, manliness isn’t toxic, and we aren’t being bullies to other men. i know this isn’t politically correct to say, but your job as a man shouldn’t be to be sensitive and be hurt by everything said to you. a virtue i have learned recently is that sticking up for yourself gets you a lot further than waiting for someone else stick to up for you. manliness isnt anything to be ashamed of. its sexist to say that you aren’t allowed to be one. @gillette thinks that men are just naturally trash and that we have to use their product to not be pieces of shit. anyway gn y’all sorry for gettin political on ya ✌🏽
