text:
healing from sexual abuse.

we can no longer pretend that everything is fine or that we can heal in our spare time. 
we have to prepare for it and make a plan.

one way to start is by becoming aware of things in our day to day life that drains our energy.

then eliminate or reduce whatever it is that drains your energy.

be sure to leave a comment below if you agree and visit https://breakingcalm.com/5minutes to get started on your healing journey.

you can also find additional inspiration on my facebook page https://www.facebook.com/reneekingbreakingcalm

#breakingcalm

text:
saying it wanted to ‘challenge men to think about the way they treat women’, social justice company gillette has released a cute new pack of pink razors, especially designed for the ladies.

at a special launch of the new product, a gillette spokesperson said the company was excited about changing the conversation around gender. “for too long men have turned a blind eye to the sexism that surrounds them. and the new daisy venus embrace pink razor is just gorgeous. am i right girls?” he said it was important for men to understand that they need to treat women equally, and that the new pink razors would cost 15% more than the blue version of the product.

as part of the special campaign that leverages the sentiment of the #metoo movement, 100% of all proceeds from the new razors will go directly to the company’s bottom line. #gillette #gillettead #metoo

text:
i think this saudi teenager perfectly personifies the cosmic phenomenon occurring right now.
we are being given the power to move mountains as the old structures die away and new rules are written.
first, four planets in their home signs adding extra weight to their character, are in natural alignment and emphatic.
then, all planets in direct motion #apdm for two whole months providing major drive for progress. 
and also, mars in aries = raaaaahh...trining venus in sag, the brave girl with a cause, fleeing her captors.
and then betwixt the eclipses.
as the solar eclipse in capricorn last week enhances the powers of both saturn and pluto to deconstruct the dominating structures in our lives and world, the upcoming lunar eclipse in leo, is a doorway for us to step through as our sovereign selves, not as minions or worker ants.
the eclipses herald a process that enhances and enables saturn and pluto in capricorn to tear down the oldest institutions across the globe from banking to europe to ancient and inbred patriarchy, and to work force drudgery and slavery to ‘the system’. saturn and pluto’s connection will continue all year to culminate in a final showdown in january 2020.
so this girl has made a mega move in calling out the legal passive aggression and inequality for women in parts of the world and her courageous call has been answered (by canada). normally this type of manoeuvre would have been unsuccessful or violently quashed, but she has all these other planetary aspects at her back, 
we have some amazing good fortune opening up, beyond what we can imagine...but this is at the expense of the old guard, whose importance and authority are no longer relevant or appropriate.
#thekingisdeadlonglivetheking

text:
en kold vinterdag i år 2010 kom mit lille vidunder til verden, den smukkeste dreng nogensinde, men det syns alle forældre selvfølgelige. ❤
det var en hurtig, nem drømme fødsel på det lokale sygehus. 
men det hele startede med at, far skulle ringes hjem fra fængslet. 
hold nu kæft hvor var jeg dum, eller det følte jeg mig! stemplet som den unge mor, fra det lave socialt dårlige stillede miljø - under den danske middelklasse. æv! men sådan var det nu engang, han sad inde for en gammel sag. 
en sag han i første omgang kun fik 30 dage for, men han mente jo selvfølgelig ikke de kunne bevise det var ham. så idioten (trods han var dømt for noget mildere, end hvad han faktisk havde lavet) ankede,  og fik 6 måneder. 🤦‍♀️ han blev kaldt ind til afsoning som min graviditet rakte mod enden, alle indlæggelser og sygehus besøg måtte jeg klare alene. mens han stadig havde en forventning om jeg trofast, stod ventende, både lørdag og søndag, når den store låge blev åbnet og til besøgs tiden sluttede. 
og det gjorde jeg selvfølgelige, for hvor ville jeg dog være en forfærdelig kæreste hvis jeg ikke gjorde. det sagde han aldrig, men jeg følte det. 
i det skjulte var der så mange forventninger at leve op til. 
hans celle kammerat blev løsladt, men havde ingen til at køre ham hjem, det blev min opgave. 
det blev lovede på mine vegne, og jeg skulle. 
så der var jeg, i sne vejr, højgravid, med bækkenløsning og lige udskrevet fra endnu et besøg på sygehuset, bag rettet på bilen med sommerdæk for at tilfredsstille ham. 
hvorfor? 
han havde jo lovet ham det, så hvilken situation ville jeg ikke sætte ham o hvis jeg afslog? 
nå tilbage min søns fødselsdag. der lå han så lille fin og gude smuk, på barselsgangen. jeg sad og betragtede ham, og var helt høj på baby'rusen, boblende af lykke - alene. 
2 timer efter fødslen skulle far tilbage til fængslet. 
har aldrig følt mig så alene, som lige der. det lille menneske, var nu vores opgave at passe på og elske, allerede der var både han og jeg efterladt. 
det var ham der var i fængsel, men jeg var den der følte mig fængslet. 
#brydtabuet #metoo #baby #newborn #fængslet #delebørn #kampen #slutnu #fortid #tanker #bearbejderminfortid #lettinggo

✨ boys will be boys ✨
▿
that statement is something that has been stewing a lot lately. the complete and utter denial of responsibility.
▿
hannah gadsby has addressed this well and so have many other women. it is so rare to hear a mens voice speak the same truths though.
▿
this video really hit home.
▿
it is very rare that a large company like gillette would create such a video that could potentially lose them customers. i'm not underestimating their awareness that women do most of purchasing so this may actually gain them customers. but either way, they haven't made light of a very real issue within our culture.
▿
i have long been known to call men out on their bs. and after a couple of drinks i get pretty direct. especially when i see a woman at the other end of it.
▿
the thing that really gets me is that other men are always standing by watching. laughing. or just keeping quiet because they don't want to be "that guy".
▿
well it's about time that things started changing.
▿
us women have enough sh*t to worry about!

text:
#metoo “the bravest of women 
all over the world,
uniting as one;
an army of girls.
their voices
once silent;
diminished and quiet.
it is hard now
to silence the roar,
of our riot.
not ever again;
no!
we will not 
be silenced.
we will not
shrink down.
we will not 
be quiet.
you will squirm at the thought 
of what we’ve been through.
and you can thank your lucky stars 
if you are lucky enough,
to be able to say 
that it never happened 
to you. 
the nightmare we lived;
the things we survived.
some days, 
the pain still cuts me so deep,
that i am barely able 
to open my eyes;
let alone
have the bravery,
to not run and hide;
the strength 
to let anyone 
see beyond my walls;
to view the horror,
of what’s still left inside.
what will it take?
how many 
of these stories
still need to be told, 
before people get it?
before this world,
is alive and woke?
those of us 
who have suffered;
our eyes 
have never been closed.
we’ve been forced 
to keep them open;
many of us, 
since only four or five years old.
and we always carry 
these memories with us;
the nightmares, and the shame.
and for so very many of us;
we were told, 
that we were to blame.
it’s hard to describe this pain 
that i feel.
hearing all these stories;
it truly is the worst kind of surreal.
to be able to comfort
and validate each other;
to know deep down, 
that we are truly not alone.
yet still somehow wishing,
it never happened to another;
not to any girl or woman;
not to any daughter or mother.
my bones are aching.
my knees are shaking.
my voice is cracking,
but i will keep on speaking;
as my tears 
continue to flow like a river,
from the very core, of my being.
we are safe here,
in each other’s stories.
we are lovingly cradled,
as we link 
arm in arm;
as we begin to connect,
shattered heart, to shattered heart.
as we reach out 
for each other’s hand. 
we are warriors,
and we are mighty.
we are a force 
to be reckoned with;
no longer will our pain 
be taken so lightly.
you never know the power,
of what sharing your story can do.
and although we are stronger,
as we all band together;
my heart is still broken,
over every, #metoo @therealmariskahargitay @thejhf @nomoreorg
name: Sarah Kacala
tweet_full:
#metoo “the bravest of women 
all over the world,
uniting as one;
an army of girls.
their voices
once silent;
diminished and quiet.
it is hard now
to silence the roar,
of our riot.
not ever again;
no!
we will not 
be silenced.
we will not
shrink down.
we will not 
be quiet.
you will squirm at the thought 
of what we’ve been through.
and you can thank your lucky stars 
if you are lucky enough,
to be able to say 
that it never happened 
to you. 
the nightmare we lived;
the things we survived.
some days, 
the pain still cuts me so deep,
that i am barely able 
to open my eyes;
let alone
have the bravery,
to not run and hide;
the strength 
to let anyone 
see beyond my walls;
to view the horror,
of what’s still left inside.
what will it take?
how many 
of these stories
still need to be told, 
before people get it?
before this world,
is alive and woke?
those of us 
who have suffered;
our eyes 
have never been closed.
we’ve been forced 
to keep them open;
many of us, 
since only four or five years old.
and we always carry 
these memories with us;
the nightmares, and the shame.
and for so very many of us;
we were told, 
that we were to blame.
it’s hard to describe this pain 
that i feel.
hearing all these stories;
it truly is the worst kind of surreal.
to be able to comfort
and validate each other;
to know deep down, 
that we are truly not alone.
yet still somehow wishing,
it never happened to another;
not to any girl or woman;
not to any daughter or mother.
my bones are aching.
my knees are shaking.
my voice is cracking,
but i will keep on speaking;
as my tears 
continue to flow like a river,
from the very core, of my being.

text:
my #10yearchallenge & #20yearchallenge, accepted! though i have changed, some things have not: i continue to love telling stories through plays that challenge me and audiences. it’s 2019: so, here’s 2009 & 1999. i remember each of these plays as if it were yesterday (the one on the right really was, well, day before yesterday).
common threads... each of these characters is a strong english woman, each of these plays challenges norms, bridges divides, reaches for truth, across generations, cultures, and, like life itself, is funny and moving and unexpected in its conclusions. they challenge us to look beyond, to break down barriers to understanding, to grow and to love.  i’m fortunate to have been a part of each. ♥️🎭 left, 20 years ago, in 1999, as flora crewe in tom stoppard’s indian ink (with faran tahir, left), directed by joy zinoman at the studio theatre, photo by carol pratt. (bonus: i had just met my love @markjberman 🎹💕) ♥️🎭
center, 10 years ago, in 2009, as lydia freemantle in @cusicram’s a lifetime burning, directed by pam mackinnon at @primarystages, photo by james leynse.
♥️🎭
right, now, 2019, this past ‪monday night‬, as m in anna ziegler’s sat nam, with clea alsip, directed by tyne rafaeli, as part of the pussy grabber plays at @joespub, a joyous evening of short plays to benefit new york women’s foundation and #metoo movement, bowing to the goddesses who have spoken out about the sexual abuse they endured by the president, produced by kate pines and team, available royalty-free to schools and organizations, to educate through theatre, photo by jenny anderson.
•
•
•

text:
sometimes you read something that so outrages you, you have to do something. but how often do we feel impotent and unable to make a difference? after i read about the despicable situation that dozens of our pole sisters were subjected to, via @jordankensley and @cerclecheung, i was enraged, especially when i found out that this hack-photographer would use his background as a martial artist (i vomit in my mouth using that term to describe this predator) to intimidate his clients.

i shared their posts in support and solidarity, but i wanted to do more. what could i offer? how could i help those vulnerable in our community and beyond?

while i know that something like that abuse can, and most likely, will happen again, i know that i can offer some knowledge borne out of years of rigorous training. i am so grateful that @xpoleus wanted to make a difference too and partner with me to offer free community events so that money will never be a barrier for a dancer from receiving some training and help.

please join me on saturday, 1/26 at x-pole headquarters 4pm-5:30pm for a free workshop about basic self-defense for all dancers. please feel free to share with those at your studio and social media :) #poledance #poledancers #poledancersofig #supportdancers #selfdefense #polefitness #polesport #pole #exoticpole #xpole #blackbelt #taekwondo #knowledgeispower #blackbeltgirl #womensdefense #believewomen #metoo

text:
this is our #guysgroup post-evaluation form completed by an 8th grade student and group participant. 
___________________________

most know that my day job consists of managing a #preventioneducation program where our dynamic educators meet with teens to talk about healthy relationships, consent and supporting victims of domestic and sexual violence. 
____________________________

our award-winning guys group program provides space for boys to discuss the #manbox and learn about sexual harassment and assault. our groups are deliberately on the binary and structured so it’s a safe space for boys to process together the ways they’ve been taught and socialized to think about masculinity, gender and sexuality. 
____________________________

we partner with schools and community organizations and ask that they identify boys who are leaders and who will influence change among their peers. 
____________________________

right now we are hiring for two guys group facilitators who can hold space with boys, build rapport, challenge them and hold them accountable to change that will ultimately eliminate violence against women, girls and gender-expansive folks. if you know someone in the st. louis area (or knows someone who knows someone) who may be interested in applying for these positions, have them contact me for more information. 
___________________________

and if you know someone @gillette, tell ‘em to get at me. 😉😝 #lbvs #sexualassaultprevention #domesticviolenceprevention #stlouis  #gillette #thebestmencanbe #metoo

text:
🌟 meet #ywrnewyork speaker senator jessica ramos! get your conference tickets today (link in bio). 🌟 
jessica ramos has spent her life fighting for working families, advocating for labor, and organizing her local community. born in elmhurst to an undocumented seamstress and a printing pressman, jessica was raised in astoria, attended queens public schools, and now lives in jackson heights with her two sons.

a strong union advocate, ramos worked with build up nyc to fight for construction, building and hotel maintenance workers in new york city. ramos also worked with sseu local 371 and 32bj seiu, where she helped building maintenance workers, office cleaners and public schools cleaners win contracts that protected their rights, wages, and benefits.

jessica was a member of queens community board 3 and served as democratic district leader in the 39th assembly district. jessica sat on the boards of the jackson heights beautification group and farmspot, jackson heights’ community-supported agriculture (csa) program. she has received awards for her work with the lgbtq community and her advocacy on behalf of women and minority-owned businesses.

even as a teenager, jessica was outspoken against poverty and the internal displacement of colombians. she was elected president of the nyc colombian liberal youth council in 2002 and subsequently elected president of the nyc colombian liberal party in 2005. 
most recently, jessica served as director of latino media for the city of new york. as the city’s chief latina spokesperson, jessica helped keep our city’s 1.87 million spanish-speaking residents, and the community and ethnic media at large, informed about government services and initiatives.

jessica credits her love for activism and public service to her parents, colombian immigrants who fought for and won the right to dual citizenship for colombian-americans and founded siempre colombia, a not-for-profit organization in jackson heights. @__jessicaramos__
.
.
.

text:
tonight, i went to see #onthebasisofsex. as i was acquiring my (one) glass of wine (it’s a new resolution, ok) prior to the movie, the guy serving me tried to get on my good side by saying “yeah, i hear that is a good movie”. i replied, “i am so excited to see it!”. he decided to continue “but i feel like too many women are coming to see it because of the whole #metoo movement.” i quickly informed him that i was not the one, in very formal and polite terms and proceeded to enjoy my drink and the phenomenal movie. i always knew ruth bader ginsburg was a badass but this movie truly put her on the level of hillary and elizabeth for me. i love being a woman and i love being a part of change. .
.
.
“feminism ... i think the simplest explanation, and one that captures the idea, is a song that marlo thomas sang, "free to be you and me." free to be, if you were a girl — doctor, lawyer, indian chief. anything you want to be. and if you’re a boy, and you like teaching, you like nursing, you would like to have a doll, that’s ok too. that notion that we should each be free to develop our own talents, whatever they may be, and not be held back by artificial barriers — man-made barriers, certainly not heaven sent.” - #rbg
.
.
“one day i’ll be gone, the world will keep turning, i hope i leave this place better than i found it.” 🎶

text:
day 217. okay, witches, the new gillette ad is good. in a world that offers *so fucking little* for women in terms of adverts that make us think and talk and slowly change minds on sexism, patriachy and misogyny, we’ll accept their good intentions and admit we shed a widdle tear and it’d be sorta churlish to criticise it too much. 
and yet. the ad also makes witches uncomfortable. because praising gillette feels *so much like* the thankful, ingratiating women who shower men with double-plus-choc-chip-cookies merely for ever behaving like actual humans. it really fucking does. 
also, the ad also reminds witches of what a fucken arsed-up world we’re in:
- a world where moral leadership now comes from multi-national corporations who may or may not give a fucking rats about social change instead of from those we specifically elected to care desperately about social change;
- a world where a relatively simple request for men (#notallmen) to not to act like dicks 24/7 is met with outrage and hate from men behaving like dicks 24/7; - a world where the same company that profits hugely from women’s low self-confidence and *literally planned for women to be ashamed of their body hair for profit* and charges more for pink razors and exploits poor women workers in developing countries and *still sells skin-whitening creams to women* now wins aaalll the gushy tears for *one* move in the right direction; - a world where riding on the coat-tails of the women-led, non-commercial #metoo campaign to reduce men’s violence is co-opted into just another marketing opportunity for a vast, male-led conglomerate; and
- a world where gillette knows *women do the shopping* and this ad’s for them, not men, so on top of all else it’s exploitative of the expectation women do the hard, unequal graft of keeping a household running, including responsibility for men’s whiskeriness (or otherwise). yeah ... nah. in our humbly witchy opinion, gillette is getting a goddamn spangly parade here for doing the kind of advertising that should be ubiquitous. the kind of advertising men shouldn’t get the fucking chance to protest because it’s all there fucking is. yes?

text:
whenever a new year rolls around, i can’t help but think of the past.
*
*
the countless times i made the decision to stay alive.
*
*
i remember that the majority of my life was spent suffering — and healing — in silence.
*
*
well, i will not be silent.
*
*
i was able to bring together some of the most passionate, talented folks i’ve had the distinct pleasure of meeting (a majority trans* and queer cast and crew!). i can’t wait to tell you more about us.
*
*
stay tuned for the release of my first music video this april, an ode to those who suffer in silence.
*
*

text:
🌼bessel van der kolk - sexual assault: understanding & healing - new session 🌼
.
dr bessel van der kolk investigates therapy strategies for sexual trauma. he examines how sexual assault is continually lived out in the body and offers approaches for therapists and patients to help rediscover their bodies. dr van der kolk gives examples that may help recognise when clients are moving forward in therapy. he explores ways to help build tolerance to physical sensations and open up “grey areas” of the brain that become shut down.
.
dr bessel van der kolk will be presented a 2 day workshop in sydney, melbourne & brisbane this march - april. find out more at byronclinic.com
.
watch this full session 'sexual assault: understanding & healing' at wisemind.com. link in bio. 🌼

text_retweet:
for your reminder✨ #repost @thedailyhealing
・・・
#ibelieveher -
i’m not one to know what’s usually going on in the news, by choice. but the past couple of days, having this platform flooded with post after post of women rising up and sharing their voice, it was easy to be impacted by the energy. 
the libra in me that stands for justice can heavily and intensely be swallowed up by a fiery passion and consumed when i get behind a movement that i believe in. 
and i know that this is the energy that these times are needing from me, to stand up, to be a voice, for those that weren’t listened to. for those that were violated. for those that were made to feel unworthy of their no.

rape. molestation. sexual coercion. is 
is disgustingly far too common. but the conversation is necessary. this discussion is mandatory. and should no longer be hidden and made to feel shameful and embarrassed of. it’s time to heal. heal so that our future generations know better and do better. 
i can’t help but think of my son and the world he is growing in. he is being raised to know compassion and respect for all. to listen, to honor, to love unconditionally. i wonder what the world will be like for him as he gets older.. all of the women in me wants to stand up and roar with millions of others!

but i find myself witnessing in awe, of the waves that are being made. of the foundations being destroyed only to build a new. of the courage blanketing this globe.

i can only trust that the work i’ve been called to offer, will continue to be a container, a safe space, a home for those that seek to unleash their voice after lifetimes of being silenced and made to feel unworthy and not good enough.

i am here. 
i am here.
i am here.

i see you
i hear you
and 
i believe you!

#metoo
#rise

text:
simply aping what men do, won't really get us much far and neither would it change the world. we would just have more of what we have - leaders corrupted by power, driven by hierarchies, dictated by dogmas, and societies following the inhuman frameworks which form culture, religion, politics and economics of today. women might get recruited into the armies and frontline combat but we need women who would rethink these structures of national armies which propogate violence and reimagine a world devoid of wars. women might break the glass cielings and enter boardrooms but there we need women who would help reimagine work and renumeration as we know it and change the cut-throat, competitive environments of corporations. sameness will help us trick patriarchy into including more women under it's umbrella but it won't smash it. feminism is about imagining a better world not just finding our space in the world we know of today.

text:
today i took a huge leap of faith literally. it took me 5 mins to stop all the negative stories i had swimming around in my head, and all the what ifs. i grabbed hold of that inflatable mattress and jumped. man alive!!! whan an adrenaline rush. if you don't do it, youll never know, you'll never know the fun you may have, or the experience of a lifetime that you may only get one chance to take. i flew down that rockslide not once but twice, and i am so happy that i took that chance and dived in, because i know deep down inside i would have had huge regrets if i had backed down. it was also a lesson for my daughter, that it's ok to feel nervous, but you won't know until you try something. (i didnt push, or let her go down today because of the water level), but the lesson was still there. this can be applied to everyday life, if you don't try something you'll never know. we spend so much time waiting, wanting, then talking ourselves out of things and we miss out on so many cool experiences, and opportunities, whether it's going down a slide, a different job, a new relationship, even a new food. so next time instead of talking yourself out of something, try talking yourself into it, my journey of creating my own happiness would never have happened if i hadn't of tried something different and said yes.
❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🧘‍♀️🚗🏞️🦋🦄👩‍👧🏊‍♀️🌈🤸‍♀️

text:
‪mr. sonu nigam’s latest interview baffles me. he says he ‘supports’ the me too movement because he has sisters & a mother (!) & ‘does not support’ anu malik’s sexual predatory ways but ‘supports’ his right to earn his livelihood inspite of these perverted actions over the years coming to light. he knows what it feels to be jobless & therefore no one should be deprived of work (& a lux life?) he adds. ‬
-i recommend  that sonu nigam’s bleeding heart set up a fund for all the wrong-doers & their families asap. -i also recommend that sonu nigam upgrade his vocabulary to understand what constitutes ‘filthy’ language.
-i also request mr nigam to lend his super powered visionary glasses with which he is able to ‘see the face’ & assess the ‘state of mind’ of others writing posts in their homes. he should patent these glasses & sell them for loads of money so that the fund he has started for the wrong-doers including those in the jails of india is forever flushed with money? also ensure that the families of such wrong-doers never lift a finger to earn their own living. 
that would solve a lot of the heart ache of mr. nigam in one go? -also, i must add that i do feel bad that he has retired from professional singing since 2006. (his words in the interview not mine) his singing skills are of no ordinary nature & this i stand by today & always. maybe he can start classes so that the younger generation actually benefit from his golden legacy? his woke stand on gender issues is not doing the trick so maybe this will help society in some way. 
i would be happy to enroll in his singing classes. 
please note that this movement of #metoo doesn’t need anyone’s fake support & shoddy lip service. we need both men & women of integrity to fight for the right thing for a safer, better future for all of us. families, societies, industries & fraternities need to be conscious & responsible. the courts cannot be the only ones deciding & defining appropriate behaviour amongst us people. 
a better answer to the last q to the interview should have been - “i’m sorry i used such language. i got my man ego get the better of me.”🙏🏽🔴
#india #change #love #opinion

text_retweet:
🔴 should all states do this to ensure fairness?🔵 state lawmakers in south dakota introduced a bill this week that would require students, who consider themselves to be transgender, to participate in school sports that correspond to their assigned biological sex, not of the gender they have assumed.

the new bill would rescind current rules adopted by the south dakota high school activities association in 2015 that allows transgender kids to participate in school sports under their assumed sexual choice, instead of their biological gender, the daily wire reported.

the bill was introduced tuesday by republicans senator jim bolin (canton) and representative thomas brunner (nisland.) sen. bolin, a former canton mayor and athletic director of the canton public schools, said his goal was to emulate recent rules in texas. “texas’ university interscholastic league requires that students participate on sports teams that correspond with the sex listed on their birth certificate,” bolin said. “it’s all about fair competition,” he added. “i just firmly believe that those who are males should play in sports designated for males, and those who are females should play in sports designated for females, according to your birth certificate. it’s about fair competition, and we’re not breaking any new ground.  the sen. said, “this has nothing to do with bathrooms, locker rooms or shower rooms. this has only to do with the eligibility for athletic competition.” repost @wearebreitbart

text:
поговорим о ценностях.

один очень известный психолог начал свой семинар по психологии, подняв вверх 500-рублевую купюру. в зале собралось около 200 человек. психолог спросил, кто хочет получить купюру. все, как по команде, подняли руки. прежде чем один из вас получит эту купюру, я кое-что с ней сделаю, — продолжил психолог. он скомкал купюру и затем спросил, хочет ли кто-нибудь все ещё её получить. и опять все подняли руки. тогда, — ответил он, — я делаю следующее, и, бросив купюру на пол, слегка повозил её ботинком по грязному полу. затем он поднял купюру, купюра была мятая и грязная. «ну кому из вас она нужна в таком виде?» и все опять подняли руки.

дорогие друзья, — сказал психолог, — только что вы получили ценный, наглядный урок. несмотря на всё то, что я проделал с купюрой, вы все хотели ее получить, так как она не потеряла своей ценности. она всё ещё купюра достоинствoм в 500 рублей.

в нашей жизни часто случается, что мы оказываемся выброшенными из седла, растоптанными, лежащими на полу или в полном дерьме. это реалии нашей жизни. в таких ситуациях мы чувствуем себя никчемными. но не важно, что случилось или случится, ты никогда не потеряешь своей ценности. грязная или чистая, помятая или отутюженная — ты всегда будешь бесценным для всех тех, кто тебя любит. наша ценность определяется не тем, что мы делаем или с кем мы знакомы, а тем — какой ты.

text:
to all boy, guys, men and gentlemen. the gender with the penis’.... this is your psa
if you ever ask a women, “hey can i ask you something?” then follow it up with, “but you can’t get mad tho.”
here’s the thing. if you have to have a fucking disclaimer before your gawd damn question... then don’t fucking ask it!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! i hate this shit that some fukwad wants to tell me something but then gets a pissy tantrum when i shut his ass down and put him in his damn place. i maybe at work but think again mother fucker, because i will still tell you to shut the fuck up and leave my store.
so here’s the story
a customer comes through my line and asks for cigarettes. i have to go to the next register for the cig case. since i’m short i have to step on the spot for the trash can so i can reach
i walk around and he asks me if he can ask a question i can’t get mad. 😒
me-ok, fine what is it????
him-how big is your waist? what are your measurements?
me-what?!!!! that’s non of your damn business and it doesn’t even matter?!!!
him-it’s just a question that’s all
me-if you even had to tell me that i shouldn’t get mad with a question then you shouldn’t have asked me. now that’s your fault! and who the hell are you?!! you’re not my husband or a damn thing to me. you can now leave my store. omg who the fuck do you think you are??!!!
him-damn. fine, i’m finna get the fuck outta here.
i’m still a little pissed about that. and it’s not the first time this month!!!
how is it that they think this shit is ok? well it’s not!!!!!!! and of all things. i’m wearing my damn work uniform, slacks and an h-e-b polo. how the hell am i calling attention or “asking” for it??!!! #metoo #enough

*almost 90%of rape cases in thailand go unreported to the authorities* “women in thailand should not have to be silent about rape and assault any longer,” she says. “it’s time people started talking about consent.” thaiconsent is a project that began as a series of articles explaining the concept of sexual consent to the founder's friends.

in the past 12 months it has grown into an online platform containing hundreds of stories of rape and assault, and inspired an exhibition of artworks designed to challenge thailand’s culture of misunderstanding over sexual assault.

text:
⁣⁣ ⁣  fear is a liar ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
many years ago fear told me i wouldn’t survive another trauma at the hands of someone i love. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
in 2013 fear told me that i wouldn’t be able to stop using the very thing i found to help me through that trauma. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣in 2015 fear told me i wouldn’t be a successful drug and alcohol counselor because i probably couldn’t even get into that program. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
in 2018 fear told me that i wouldn’t know how to get back up... again.⁣⁣
⁣⁣ fear. is. a. liar. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
empower your life and write your fear story. you don’t have to share it but you must do it. the idea is to write about how fear lied to you and you showed up to change the ending. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
look at yourself surviving. ⁣⁣
look at yourself killing it at life. ⁣⁣
look at yourself still loving the hell out of this world. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#youareenough ⁣⁣
#iamenough

text: oh hi. i’ve had an awful head cold and have been feeling pretty rotten the last couple days. i’ve also spent more time on instagram lately reading than posting because of an important discussion about racism in the knitting/maker community. it’s been illuminating and heartbreaking to listen to these women of colour talk about how they have been treated and made to feel othered and invisible. i have a lot of thoughts about this but not a lot that i want to say here because i’ve dubbed it “white noise” when white women start trying to make the discussion about them. all i can say is just like in the #metoo movement: listen to these women, believe these women. do better.

text:
the time i learned a new strong...
.
.
it was years ago while working at a sexual assault/domestic violence center where i truly first learned about mental health.  before, i didn’t really know a whole lot about it...it was sort of this stigma, this one-off-type-of-thing that happen to other people...not me.  i was strong.  but at this center i saw so many survivors come in and out to receive counseling and support and i was inspired by their fight and i was glad there was help for others...but not me.  i was strong.  and then i went through a pretty awful break-up.  the kind that makes you feel broke and brittle and maybe even dangerous to yourself.  then that type-of-thing called “therapy” wasn’t just good for others...it was good for me.  but even then i couldn’t help but feel weak.
.
.
it’s amazing really.  we spend a lot of time working and improving ourselves physically, career-wise, educationally, and for some of us spiritually...but when it comes to our mental/emotional health...we’re both afraid and ashamed to find help. but sometimes it takes you to be broken and brittle to realize you need a new help.  and sometimes you can learn a lot from survivors and find the kind of inspiration you need to fight for your own life, too.  and maybe the only reason you need to to get therapy is cuz you’re human and this thing called life is crazy enough.  and maybe that shouldn’t make you afraid or ashamed at all...maybe it just makes you brave.  and if you’re like me and believe that your mental health is important then you understand...it’s not for the weak at all...it’s actually for the strong 😉💪🏾✊🏾💜. #mentalhealth is #loveyourself .
.

text:
the notorious @gillette commercial

a few seconds into the ad, we know that gillette wants to talk about the #metoo movement. an old gillette commercial plays where we see nothing but a well shaved man being kissed by a woman. this old ad shows the manner in which brands like gillette and axe have been portraying women for a long time- as objects of pleasure. 
a few frames later, we see a crowd of young boys tear through the screen playing this ad. they then proceed to run through scenes of bullying and abuse.  this portrays gillette's awareness of its own past regression. the brand wants to tear through that image and join a better world. 
though brands are often accused of capitalising on social movements, the fact remains that capitalism is a key driver when it comes to social change. the effect of ads has been known far and wide. we consume ads subconsciously and get influenced by the portrayal of people in these ads. hence, this ad which spreads the message of empathy among men, not just for women but towards each other, is an important stand against #toxicmasculinity . 
for more analyses, click the link in the about section. thanks!

a few frames later, we see a crowd of young boys tear through the screen playing this ad. they then proceed to run through scenes of bullying and abuse.  this porays gillette's awareness of its own past regression. the brand wants to tear through that image and join a better world. 
though brands are often accused of capitalising on social movements, the fact remains that capitalism is a key driver when it comes to social change. the effect of ads has been known far and wide. we consume ads subconsciously and get influenced by the porayal of people in these ads. hence, this ad which spreads the message of empathy among men, not just for women but towards each other, is an impoant stand against  .

#dontbanrkellysmusic
in 1994 we all heard kelly got aaliyah pregnant and married her when she was 15 years old. a video tape of r. kelly having sex and urinating on an alleged 14 year old was made in 1999, the tape was leaked to the public in 2000. kelly was acquitted of all charges in 2008 even though millions saw kelly on the video tape having sex with an alleged minor. this performance took place on the bet awards in 2010!

robert sylvester kelly (born january 8, 1967)  is an american singer, songwriter, record producer, and former professional basketball player. a native of chicago, kelly began performing during the late 1980s and debuted in 1992 with the group public announcement. in 1993, kelly went solo with the album 12 play. he is known for a collection of major hit singles including "bump n' grind", "your body's callin'", "i believe i can fly", "gotham city", "ignition (remix)", "if i could turn back the hands of time", "the world's greatest", "i'm a flirt (remix)", and the hip-hopera "trapped in the closet". in 1998, kelly won three grammy awards for "i believe i can fly".his distinctive sound and style has influenced numerous hip hop and contemporary r&b artists. kelly became the first musician to play professional basketball, when he was signed in 1997.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

in 1994 we all heard kelly got aaliyah pregnant and married her when she was 15 years old. a video tape of r. kelly having sex and urinating on an alleged 14 year old was made in 1999, the tape was leaked to the public in 2000. kelly was acquitted of all charges in 2008 even though millions saw kelly on the video tape having sex with an alleged minor. this performance took place on the bet awards in 2010!

robert sylvester kelly (born january 8, 1967)  is an american singer, songwriter, record producer, and former professional basketball player. a native of chicago, kelly began performing during the late 1980s and debuted in 1992 with the group public announcement. in 1993, kelly went solo with the album 12 play. he is known for a collection of major hit singles including "bump n' grind", "your body's callin'", "i believe i can fly", "gotham city", "ignition (remix)", "if i could turn back the hands of time", "the world's greatest", "i'm a flirt (remix)", and the hip-hopera "trapped in the closet". in 1998, kelly won three grammy awards for "i believe i can fly".his distinctive sound and style has influenced numerous hip hop and contemporary r&b artists. kelly became the first musician to play professional basketball, when he was signed in 1997.

text:
i woke early .. the moment of gratitude that you are the driver of your own destiny and brexit can’t ruin it today and or any other day ! 
the media camped outside parliament and endless conversations that have very little hope attached to them 
i realised i am, yes me ... a woman who chose to live after sexual and physical violence & not allow the man to take anymore of my life

a woman who grew a successful businesses whilst being a single mum 
a woman who found resilience and courage to change her life and business after a serious car crash 
a woman who leads her path with soul, sass & grace .. knowing where she is going and devoted to her cause

brexit reminded me i am the leader of my life!

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

in 1994 we all heard kelly got aaliyah pregnant and married her when she was 15 years old. a video tape of r. kelly having sex and urinating on an alleged 14 year old was made in 1999, the tape was leaked to the public in 2000. kelly was acquitted of all charges in 2008 even though millions saw kelly on the video tape having sex with an alleged minor. this performance took place on the bet awards in 2010!

robert sylvester kelly (born january 8, 1967)  is an american singer, songwriter, record producer, and former professional basketball player. a native of chicago, kelly began performing during the late 1980s and debuted in 1992 with the group public announcement. in 1993, kelly went solo with the album 12 play. he is known for a collection of major hit singles including "bump n' grind", "your body's callin'", "i believe i can fly", "gotham city", "ignition (remix)", "if i could turn back the hands of time", "the world's greatest", "i'm a flirt (remix)", and the hip-hopera "trapped in the closet". in 1998, kelly won three grammy awards for "i believe i can fly".his distinctive sound and style has influenced numerous hip hop and contemporary r&b artists. kelly became the first musician to play professional basketball, when he was signed in 1997.

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer".
.
in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytic until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

что мы знаем о токсичной маскулинности? новая реклама gillette вызвала бурный ажиотаж в сети. 
в ролике представители gillette призывают общественность пересмотреть свои взгляды на мужественность. в рекламном видео, явно вдохновленном идеями движения против харассмента #metoo, показываются сцены, наглядно демонстрирующие токсичную маскулинность в современном обществе. количество дизлайков в 2 раза превышает количество лайков.

следом закадровый голос спрашивает: "разве это лучшее, что может получить мужчина?" это отсылка к легендарному слогану бренда "gillette — лучше для мужчины нет" (the best man can get). в конце ролика мы слышим обновленный слоган компании: "лучший мужчина, который может быть" (the best men can be). несмотря на благие намерения бренда, запуск новой рекламной кампании и изменение слогана вызвали противоречивую реакцию.

и если одни признались, что будут покупать продукцию gillette хотя бы для того, чтобы сделать свой вклад в благотворительность, то другие посчитали ролик унизительным и осудили представителей бренда за ненужные нравоучения.

а что вы думаете про данный ролик?

text:
when we are travelling through this journey called life, we will experience different events that will bring various emotions, feelings and thoughts. 
some of them will be good, some of them will be bad and the rest of them will leave us feeling suffocated and silenced.

when we experience the feeling of suffocation and silence for too long, it begins to break us inside and as the negative emotions, feelings and thoughts build up, it begins to burn us inside - metaphorically of course.

while designing the cover of my memoir almost, i was experimenting with filters and when i came across the flame over my face effect, it helped me to understand how we feel inside where no one else can see what we are experiencing. hopefully this helps you to understand yourselves better within.

what are your thoughts?

text_retweet:
#repost @kirstengillibrand with @get_repost
・・・
tonight i announced that i’m preparing to run for president of the united states, because i believe that we’re all called to do whatever we can to make a difference and help people. i believe in right versus wrong, and that wrong wins when we do nothing. now is our time to raise our voices, fight for our beliefs and get off the sidelines.

i believe that in the face of division and hate, this country needs a movement rooted in compassion and courage. we want to be an america defined by strength of character, not weakness of ego. we need to protect and expand all of our basic rights and fight for better health care, education and jobs. and i believe i'm the woman for the job.

the campaign that we're building will have one core mission: restoring power to the people. i won’t accept contributions from corporate pacs or federal lobbyists, and i'm not afraid to take on trump, special interests or any powerful system – never have been. our movement will be about lifting up voices that have been ignored for too long and taking institutional racism and injustice head-on – in our politics, health care, education and economy. let's show what we can build with determination and optimism, rather than hatred and fear. 
this a moment in history when none of us can stay silent; we have to rise up, reclaim our values and act with compassion. at such a time as this, we all have to ask ourselves: what will we do?

i’ll fight, and i’ll fight with everything i have. it would mean so much if you joined me. (scott kowalchyk/cbs)
.
.
.

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
je commence sorcières 🧙‍♀️ 📖: “avec "sorcières", la journaliste mona chollet signe un livre très accessible, qui se révèle une passionnante réflexion sur la puissance des normes culturelles qui s'imposent à nous. en explorant l'impossible indépendance féminine, la violence de l'obligation à la maternité, la péremption des femmes (et l'injonction à la jeunesse, ce "statut inférieur"...)... mona chollet explore l'hostilité qu'ont entretenus les hommes à l'égard des femmes. pourtant, il ne faudrait pas voir à ranger trop facilement le livre de mona chollet comme un pamphlet féministe de plus... sorcières va plus loin. c'est un livre qui interroge la pesanteur des normes de nos sociétés. mona chollet souligne combien le "bouc-émissaire" de nos sociétés, la sorcière, cette femme libre et indépendante, n'est pas une construction des classes populaires, mais une construction sociale, qui provient avant tout des classes cultivées. de la sorcière à #metoo, elle montre l'empreinte du patriarcat sur nos consciences, comment les hommes ont pris le pouvoir, pour imposer leur façon de voir le monde. ce ne sont pas seulement les femmes que notre culture a reléguée, c'est aussi une sensibilité différente, distinctive. mais plus qu'une sensibilité, ce qu'on a rejeté, c'est une autre manière de voir le monde. en chassant les femmes indépendantes, c'est un autre rapport au monde qu'on a fait disparaître, un autre rapport au savoir, au profit d'une science arrogante et au détriment d'une nature qu'il s'agissait de dominer. derrière la chasse aux guérisseuses, derrière l'infantilisation et l'instrumentalisation des femmes, mona chollet lie cette guerre, ce sexisme, à quelque chose qui le dépasse : à la manière dont les hommes (contre les femmes) ont imposé le culte de la rationalité, cette manière d'envisager le monde, d'organiser la connaissance et la façon dont nous agissons sur le monde et dont nous le transformons.”
.
.
.
#sorcières #book #bookstagram #lecture #livre #lire #feminism #women #men #tomorrow #heforshe #alltogether #society #change #reco #home #inspiration #culture

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day.

michelle nichols
reuters

it's an uncomfortable conversation but not as uncomfortable as actually going through it ma dude.

struggle street.
big fucking #metoo
the tea is i was sexually abused halfway through last year. there isn't really a nice way to say it because it's shit no matter which way you try flipping the coin lol. i guess i'm saying this because it fucked me up big time and i don't really want to down play how i'm doing anymore after suppressing it for so long. we share our highlights on social media but not our struggles, so ima be real. right now everything is just a bit shit and that's okay because it's a fucking shit situation. i'm out here trying to get back to feeling human. most days it's a struggle just remembering to breath, eat or sleep. i'm going through the process of recieving counseling and on going therapy, shout out to the lovely ladies at wellington rape crisis centre. you have a hard job but without you and the amazing people around me(like the human who took these photos even though i'm not really a big fan of my appearance right now due to the current situation, i'm learning to be comfortable with my photo being taken again) who remind me constantly to just just take a break (i'm trash at this,i'm learning) and look after me. it's a really shit time but not a shit life, we're all trying to survive something on top of all the other shit we've got going on, the road to recovery is a messy bitch, can confirm but damn are you loved. freshly written after having a fat cry.
congratulations if you made it to the end lol.

text:
ciągle mnie trzyma dyskusja wokół konkursu ams. w komentarzach pod postami i artykułami dotyczącymi szkodliwych efektów plakatów mnóstwo było niestety nienawiści i pogardy. była fatfobia i bodyshaming. i było jeszcze coś: kwestionowanie uczuć i doświadczeń innych osób. pod prawdziwymi historiami osób dzielących się swoimi przeżyciami i opowiadających o swoich traumach, które te plakaty przywoływały na nowo, znalazło się pełno komentarzy z serii „nie rozumiem oburzenia, chętnie powiesiłabym sobie taki plakat w kuchni” albo „ja jestem otyła i jakoś mnie to nie dotyka, przesadzasz”.
.
takie wypowiedzi są niestety częste w przeróżnych kontekstach – spotykam je też regularnie chociażby w dyskusjach o przemocy. osoba dzieli się swoją historią, a w odpowiedzi słyszy, że „to nie może być takie złe”, bo ktoś inny „nie widzi problemu”. serio, opowiadanie o traumach czy dyskryminacji, jakiej się doświadcza, jest wystarczająco trudne bez tego. jako ludzie doświadczamy różnych rzeczy. czasami doświadczamy rzeczy bardzo podobnych, ale nadal możemy różnie je odczuwać. to, że ciebie coś nie dotyka, nie znaczy, że inna osoba „jest przewrażliwiona”. słuchając siebie nawzajem i wierząc w historie innych możemy budować bezpieczną przestrzeń. podważając uczucia i doświadczenia innych – co najwyżej ranić.
.
[teskt z grafiki: „nie kwestionuj uczuć i doświadczeń innych osób”]

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
why hasn’t #metoo come for ian connor? to date, six women have publicly accused former kanye west creative consultant of rape. recently, he launched a new clothing label, starred in magazine editorials (numéro magazine proclaimed him one of the “coolest it-boys of the moment” earlier this month), and attended top fashion shows, sitting front-row at virgil abloh’s debut show for louis vuitton last summer. “nothing has happened. and just as of recently he’s been more and more and more put in the media and pop culture, he’s kind of found his way back into being socially accepted,” says jean deaux, who first made public allegations against connor in april 2016.

muna mire, a writer and associate producer on television show desus & mero, tweeted last week: “did ian connor face literally any consequences i feel like i still see him in the background of virgil’s instagrams?????” connor was quick to respond: “if the consequences were more money, more power, and a clearer head space then yes. i did face the consequences,” he tweeted back.

bof managed to reach three of the six women who had publicly accused connor of raping them. they each reaffirmed their allegations. read the full story on businessoffashion.com [link in bio] 📷: @gettyimages

text:
at the shout! network, we basically, constantly, consistently, customarily shout!

just another thursday in the office (except that it's never 'just' that) and our chief eye/brain/mind opener @potato_potahtoe_ @my_bookrack  passes on a packet of chocolate nutties and a youtube link to gillette's newest "we believe" advertisement, to appease mid-morning munchies for the stomach and brain, all at once.

we watch it. we realize the internet has gone wild. it should. we have. the jungle is here, in our office, first, before anywhere else.

there are men who are impressed and men who are pissed off and men who're all charged up and men who're indifferent and just want to eat their chocolate and use their razors.

there are women who've jumped out of their seats, yelling (shout!ing), with every known expletive, that this is finally 2019; that this is revolutionary.

and whether this is a marketing masterstroke or a fluke or a true awakening, it is bloody brilliant.

a brand, that for years has prided itself on giving men "the best they can get", the apex of masculinity, transforms their campaign from a statement to a question. is this the best men can get? is this the best men can be?

and they "believe" and affirm that they'll help men find the best they can be.

why're some of the men sitting at our round table mad? 
because they don't want to be schooled by a razor.

are they forgetting, some lessons often cut like a blade? 
lick your wounds boys.
you can be better. trust us, you can.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kopmueyp3a0

but shout! to/at/with us anyway... it's www.theshoutnetwork.com @theshoutnetwork 
#revolution #heforshe #feminism #metoo #metoomovement #time #thisisit #change #transformation #brand #rebranding #masterstroke #shout #excited #2019 #here #now

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text: #metoo : यौन शोषण के आरोप में फंसे #राजकुमारहिरानी को #जावेदअख्तर का समर्थन.... #संजू की अस्सिटेंड डायरेक्टर रही एक महिला द्वारा राजकुमार हिरानी पर मार्च 2018 से सितंबर 2018 के बीच कई बार उसका यौन शोषण करने के संगीन आरोप लगाने के बाद जावेद अख्तर ने अपने सोशल मीडिया अकाउंट से एक हिरानी के समर्थन में एक पोस्ट लिखा है। पोस्ट में अख्तर लिखते हैं, ‘मैं फ़िल्म उद्योग में वर्ष 1965 में आया था, इतने वर्षों बाद अगर कोई मुझसे पूछे कि करीब पांच दशकों में आप इस उद्योग में जिन लोगों से मिले, उनमें सबसे सभ्य कौन है, तो शायद पहला नाम मेरे जहन में राजू हिरानी का होगा. जी. बी. शॉ ने कहा है, "बहुत ज्यादा अच्छा होना भी बहुत खतरनाक है"। हालांकि आरोप लगाने वाली महिला का कहना है कि उसने #विधुविनोदचोपड़ा को मेल लिख कर अपने साथ हुए यौन शोषण की शिकायत की थी. इसके अलावा उसने चोपड़ा की पत्नी अनुपमा चोपड़ा, स्क्रिप्ट राइटर अभिजीत जोशी, विधु विनोद चोपड़ा की बहन और डायरेक्टर शैली चोपड़ी को यौन शोषण के बारे में जानकारी दी थी. लेकिन इस बारे में कुछ नहीं किया गया। share your thoughts on the issue...

text:
@thepiersmorgan 
feel hard done by do you?your masculinity which you so cherish is being threatened is it? do you feel innately infuriated, hard done by in society?treated unfairly dare i say unequal?well sir welcome to the world of a woman.we have been dealing with your precious masculinity since the beginning of time. you want to know why gillette’s message has changed....because the times change, society changes , it grows , it evolves. it attempts to weed out imperfections, and im sorry but if you are not  happy with teaching the younger generation to respect and not objectify woman, intervene and attempt to stop bullying and to be able to show emotion as well as teaching our young men that they are so much more powerful and effective in society without violence, without being shamed then sir you are an even bigger twat than i thought. to men who feel their position is threatened in society. take a moment to understand why this is happening. one of the most beautiful and skilful things any human being can do is attempt to empathise particularly in situations they are unfamiliar with. i can’t speak for all woman nor will i attempt to but i can with confidence speak for a large proportion, and what i would like to say is this. there is no innate hate generated from a woman towards a man, this is not pre programmed, we as women work very similarly to yourselves, we have to have something happen to us that is negative to cause a reaction, when this happens enough times to enough women i believe you can understand why certain things happen such as the #metoo movement, when there is too much boiling water in the pot then it has nothing left to do but overflow. you can be as masculine as you want, but it’s how you use this masculinity within society that is being addressed. i know personally some phenomenal men, that have had a huge impact and influence on my life, i have been lucky enough to have them in my world and show me the true meaning of what it is to be a man. women aren’t perfect, but we don’t claim to be. the problem is this statement is redundant in an argument when it is used simply as a means of deflection. #gilletteadvert

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
rise and shine ... it’s breakfast time! and i can think of nothing better than a traditional french crepe! #asoulsurvivordesserts #asoulsurvivorbreakfast
.
my brother @caseycrookston served a mission for #thechurchofjesuschristoflatterdaysaints  in paris and brought back this crepe recipe with him. this is the real deal you guys! don’t thank me, let’s all thank the french! 😉 🇫🇷 this recipe can easily be halved!
.
- 3 cups flour
- 8 eggs
- 4 cups skim milk
- 3/4 cup sugar
- 3 tbsp oil
- 3 tbsp vanilla
.
mix all ingredients together and let sit for half an hour before cooking in a crepe pan.
.
if using a 1/3 cup measurement it will make about 24 crepes.
.
calories per crepe: 134
f:3.5 c:20.2 p:5

text:
sim! hoje é dia de reflexão!

sempre desconfio de resoluções simples para problemas complexos. geralmente quando escuto algo do tipo, algumas coisas me vêm: - mas se é tão simples, por que não fizeram antes?
- se é tão fácil, por que virou um problema? não conseguiram prever?
- por que essa pessoa está me dizendo isso enquanto o problema ainda está acontecendo?

se pegarmos alguma solução simples para um problema complexo e fizermos minimamente estas três questões, teremos que tipo de resposta?

problemas complexos, requerem pensamentos críticos também complexos e, quando a resolução é possível, também será complexa.

podemos pensar por exemplo em transtornos psicológicos, como o transtorno do estresse pós-traumático, pânico, ansiedade, depressão. não é só fazer terapia e tomar medicação. as dimensões e análises nesses exemplos são tão complexas que não caberiam nos caracteres daqui. 
mas podemos pensar em outras questões também. tais como segurança pública, saúde, educação, direitos humanos e por aí vai! 
não se nasce sabendo pensar criticamente. esta é uma habilidade aprendida e aprimorada ao longo de anos. lembre-se disso!

e, se precisar de algo, pode contar comigo!

#psicologia #psicoterapiaindividual #psicoterapiaonline #psico #brasil #brazil#autoestima #autoconfiança #amor #equilibrio #coragem #analisedocomportamento #terapiaonline #psicolink #bemestar #nemumaamenos #metoo #heforshe #terapiafeminista #feminismo #feminism #frustrações #saúdemental #emoções #frustração #resiliencia #pensamentocritico

text:
~quels sont les blocages engendrés par la société sur la liberté corporelle et sexuelle des femmes ? dans cet écrit je témoigne de mon expérience en tant que femme, de certains blocages et certaines difficultés que j'ai surmonté et la manière dont j'y suis parvenue... ~
je suis si heureuse de vous presenter un petit aperçu du travail d'écriture que j'ai mené pendant plusieurs mois. travail qui a été émotionnellement difficile et éprouvant mais qui, enfin, prend forme... je suis si fière d'avoir trouvé le courage d'aller jusqu'au bout, car je pense, malgré la difficulté, qu'il est important de prendre la parole en tant que femme... non seulement pour dénoncer mais aussi et surtout pour partager des solutions/expériences qui permettent de se relever, ensembles, plus fortes...! :) encore merci a toute les personnes qui m'ont soutenues et aux femmes qui ont participés aux ateliers qui ont été de réelles sources d'inspiration... merci aux comptes instagram qui diffusent si bien le combat comme @tasjoui et @mercibeaucul_ ;) ❤

yeh yeh trop hâte de la suite ! 
ces éditions ont été réalisés pour le passage de mon dnsep et ne peuvent être vendues...
mais si mon travail vous intéressent et que vous souhaitez le lire, contactez moi en mp, je vais réfléchir à un moyen de diffusion. :) *
*
